46 object Typer {
47 
48   /** The precedence of bindings which determines which of several bindings will be
49    *  accessed by an Ident.
50    */
51   object BindingPrec {
52     val definition = 4
53     val namedImport = 3
54     val wildImport = 2
55     val packageClause = 1
56     val nothingBound = 0
57     def isImportPrec(prec: Int) = prec == namedImport || prec == wildImport
58   }
59 
60   /** Assert tree has a position, unless it is empty or a typed splice */
61   def assertPositioned(tree: untpd.Tree)(implicit ctx: Context) =
62     if (!tree.isEmpty && !tree.isInstanceOf[untpd.TypedSplice] && ctx.typerState.isGlobalCommittable)
63       assert(tree.pos.exists, s"position not set for $tree # ${tree.uniqueId}")
64 
65   /** A context property that indicates the owner of any expressions to be typed in the context
66    *  if that owner is different from the context's owner. Typically, a context with a class
67    *  as owner would have a local dummy as ExprOwner value.
68    */
69   private val ExprOwner = new Property.Key[Symbol]
70 
71   /** An attachment on a Select node with an `apply` field indicating that the `apply`
72    *  was inserted by the Typer.
73    */
74   private val InsertedApply = new Property.Key[Unit]
75 
76   /** An attachment on a tree `t` occurring as part of a `t()` where
77    *  the `()` was dropped by the Typer.
78    */
79   private val DroppedEmptyArgs = new Property.Key[Unit]
80 }

82 class Typer extends Namer
83                with TypeAssigner
84                with Applications
85                with Implicits
86                with Inferencing
87                with Dynamic

91   import Typer._
92   import tpd.{cpy => _, _}
93   import untpd.cpy
94   import Dynamic.isDynamicMethod
95   import reporting.diagnostic.Message
96   import reporting.diagnostic.messages._
97 
98   /** A temporary data item valid for a single typed ident:
99    *  The set of all root import symbols that have been
100    *  encountered as a qualifier of an import so far.
101    *  Note: It would be more proper to move importedFromRoot into typedIdent.
102    *  We should check that this has no performance degradation, however.
103    */
104   private[this] var unimported: Set[Symbol] = Set()
105 
106   /** Temporary data item for single call to typed ident:
107    *  This symbol would be found under Scala2 mode, but is not
108    *  in dotty (because dotty conforms to spec section 2
109    *  wrt to package member resolution but scalac doe not).
110    */
111   private[this] var foundUnderScala2: Type = NoType
112 
113   def newLikeThis: Typer = new Typer
114 
115   /** Attribute an identifier consisting of a simple name or wildcard
116    *
117    *  @param tree      The tree representing the identifier.
118    *  Transformations: (1) Prefix class members with this.
119    *                   (2) Change imported symbols to selections.
120    *                   (3) Change pattern Idents id (but not wildcards) to id @ _
121    */
122   def typedIdent(tree: untpd.Ident, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedIdent") {
123     val refctx = ctx
124     val name = tree.name
125     val noImports = ctx.mode.is(Mode.InPackageClauseName)
126 
127     /** Method is necessary because error messages need to bind to
128      *  to typedIdent's context which is lost in nested calls to findRef
129      */
130     def error(msg: => Message, pos: Position) = ctx.error(msg, pos)
131 
132     /** Does this identifier appear as a constructor of a pattern? */
133     def isPatternConstr =
134       if (ctx.mode.isExpr && (ctx.outer.mode is Mode.Pattern))
135         ctx.outer.tree match {
136           case Apply(`tree`, _) => true
137           case _ => false
138         }
139       else false
140 
141     /** A symbol qualifies if it really exists and is not a package class.
142      *  In addition, if we are in a constructor of a pattern, we ignore all definitions
143      *  which are methods and not accessors (note: if we don't do that
144      *  case x :: xs in class List would return the :: method).
145      *
146      *  Package classes are part of their parent's scope, because otherwise
147      *  we could not reload them via `_.member`. On the other hand, accessing a
148      *  package as a type from source is always an error.
149      */
150     def qualifies(denot: Denotation): Boolean =
151       reallyExists(denot) &&
152         !(pt.isInstanceOf[UnapplySelectionProto] &&
153           (denot.symbol is (Method, butNot = Accessor))) &&
154         !(denot.symbol is PackageClass)
155 
156     /** Find the denotation of enclosing `name` in given context `ctx`.
157      *  @param previous    A denotation that was found in a more deeply nested scope,
158      *                     or else `NoDenotation` if nothing was found yet.
159      *  @param prevPrec    The binding precedence of the previous denotation,
160      *                     or else `nothingBound` if nothing was found yet.
161      *  @param prevCtx     The context of the previous denotation,
162      *                     or else `NoContext` if nothing was found yet.
163      */
164     def findRef(previous: Type, prevPrec: Int, prevCtx: Context)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
165       import BindingPrec._
166 
167       /** Check that any previously found result from an inner context
168        *  does properly shadow the new one from an outer context.
169        *  @param found     The newly found result
170        *  @param newPrec   Its precedence
171        *  @param scala2pkg Special mode where we check members of the same package, but defined
172        *                   in different compilation units under Scala2. If set, and the
173        *                   previous and new contexts do not have the same scope, we select
174        *                   the previous (inner) definition. This models what scalac does.
175        */
176       def checkNewOrShadowed(found: Type, newPrec: Int, scala2pkg: Boolean = false)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
177         if (!previous.exists || ctx.typeComparer.isSameRef(previous, found)) found
178         else if ((prevCtx.scope eq ctx.scope) &&
179                  (newPrec == definition ||
180                   newPrec == namedImport && prevPrec == wildImport)) {
181           // special cases: definitions beat imports, and named imports beat
182           // wildcard imports, provided both are in contexts with same scope
183           found
184         }
185         else {
186           if (!scala2pkg && !previous.isError && !found.isError) {
187             error(AmbiguousImport(name, newPrec, prevPrec, prevCtx), tree.pos)
188           }
189           previous
190         }
191 
192       def selection(imp: ImportInfo, name: Name) =
193         if (imp.sym.isCompleting) {
194           ctx.warning(i"cyclic ${imp.sym}, ignored", tree.pos)
195           NoType
196         } else if (unimported.nonEmpty && unimported.contains(imp.site.termSymbol))
197           NoType
198         else {
199           val pre = imp.site
200           val denot = pre.member(name).accessibleFrom(pre)(refctx)
201             // Pass refctx so that any errors are reported in the context of the
202             // reference instead of the
203           if (reallyExists(denot)) pre.select(name, denot) else NoType
204         }
205 
206       /** The type representing a named import with enclosing name when imported
207        *  from given `site` and `selectors`.
208        */
209       def namedImportRef(imp: ImportInfo)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
210         val Name = name.toTermName
211         def recur(selectors: List[untpd.Tree]): Type = selectors match {
212           case selector :: rest =>
213             def checkUnambiguous(found: Type) = {
214               val other = recur(selectors.tail)
215               if (other.exists && found.exists && (found != other))
216                 error(em"reference to `$name` is ambiguous; it is imported twice in ${ctx.tree}",
217                       tree.pos)
218               found
219             }
220 
221             def unambiguousSelection(name: Name) =
222               checkUnambiguous(selection(imp, name))
223 
224             selector match {
225               case Thicket(fromId :: Ident(Name) :: _) =>
226                 val Ident(from) = fromId
227                 unambiguousSelection(if (name.isTypeName) from.toTypeName else from)
228               case Ident(Name) =>
229                 unambiguousSelection(name)
230               case _ =>
231                 recur(rest)
232             }
233           case nil =>
234             NoType
235         }
236         recur(imp.selectors)
237       }
238 
239       /** The type representing a wildcard import with enclosing name when imported
240        *  from given import info
241        */
242       def wildImportRef(imp: ImportInfo)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
243         if (imp.isWildcardImport && !imp.excluded.contains(name.toTermName) && name != nme.CONSTRUCTOR)
244           selection(imp, name)
245         else NoType
246 
247       /** Is (some alternative of) the given predenotation `denot`
248        *  defined in current compilation unit?
249        */
250       def isDefinedInCurrentUnit(denot: Denotation)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = denot match {
251         case MultiDenotation(d1, d2) => isDefinedInCurrentUnit(d1) || isDefinedInCurrentUnit(d2)
252         case denot: SingleDenotation => denot.symbol.sourceFile == ctx.source.file
253       }
254 
255       /** Is `denot` the denotation of a self symbol? */
256       def isSelfDenot(denot: Denotation)(implicit ctx: Context) = denot match {
257         case denot: SymDenotation => denot is SelfName
258         case _ => false
259       }
260 
261       /** Would import of kind `prec` be not shadowed by a nested higher-precedence definition? */
262       def isPossibleImport(prec: Int)(implicit ctx: Context) =
263         !noImports &&
264         (prevPrec < prec || prevPrec == prec && (prevCtx.scope eq ctx.scope))
265 
266       @tailrec def loop(lastCtx: Context)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
267         if (ctx.scope == null) previous
268         else {
269           var result: Type = NoType
270 
271           val curOwner = ctx.owner
272 
273           // Can this scope contain new definitions? This is usually the first
274           // context where either the scope or the owner changes wrt the
275           // context immediately nested in it. But for package contexts, it's
276           // the opposite: the last context before the package changes. This distinction
277           // is made so that top-level imports following a package clause are
278           // logically nested in that package clause. Finally, for the root package
279           // we switch back to the original test. This means that rop-level packages in
280           // the root package take priority over root imports. For instance,
281           // a top-level io package takes priority over scala.io.
282           // It would be nice if we could drop all this complication, and
283           // always use the second condition. Unfortunately compileStdLib breaks
284           // with an error on CI which I cannot replicate locally (not even
285           // with the exact list of files given).
286           val isNewDefScope =
287             if (curOwner.is(Package) && !curOwner.isRoot) curOwner ne ctx.outer.owner
288             else (ctx.scope ne lastCtx.scope) || (curOwner ne lastCtx.owner)
289 
290           if (isNewDefScope) {
291             val defDenot = ctx.denotNamed(name)
292             if (qualifies(defDenot)) {
293               val found =
294                 if (isSelfDenot(defDenot)) curOwner.enclosingClass.thisType
295                 else {
296                   val effectiveOwner =
297                     if (curOwner.isTerm && defDenot.symbol.isType)
298                       // Don't mix NoPrefix and thisType prefixes, since type comparer
299                       // would not detect types to be compatible. Note: If we replace the
300                       // 2nd condition by `defDenot.symbol.maybeOwner.isType` we get lots
301                       // of failures in the `tastyBootstrap` test. Trying to compile these
302                       // files in isolation works though.
303                       // TODO: Investigate why that happens.
304                       defDenot.symbol.owner
305                     else
306                       curOwner
307                   effectiveOwner.thisType.select(name, defDenot)
308                 }
309               if (!(curOwner is Package) || isDefinedInCurrentUnit(defDenot))
310                 result = checkNewOrShadowed(found, definition) // no need to go further out, we found highest prec entry
311               else {
312                 if (ctx.scala2Mode && !foundUnderScala2.exists)
313                   foundUnderScala2 = checkNewOrShadowed(found, definition, scala2pkg = true)
314                 if (defDenot.symbol is Package)
315                   result = checkNewOrShadowed(previous orElse found, packageClause)
316                 else if (prevPrec < packageClause)
317                   result = findRef(found, packageClause, ctx)(ctx.outer)
318               }
319             }
320           }
321 
322           if (result.exists) result
323           else {  // find import
324             val outer = ctx.outer
325             val curImport = ctx.importInfo
326             def updateUnimported() =
327               if (curImport.unimported.exists) unimported += curImport.unimported
328             if (ctx.owner.is(Package) && curImport != null && curImport.isRootImport && previous.exists)
329               previous // no more conflicts possible in this case
330             else if (isPossibleImport(namedImport) && (curImport ne outer.importInfo)) {
331               val namedImp = namedImportRef(curImport)
332               if (namedImp.exists)
333                 findRef(checkNewOrShadowed(namedImp, namedImport), namedImport, ctx)(outer)
334               else if (isPossibleImport(wildImport) && !curImport.sym.isCompleting) {
335                 val wildImp = wildImportRef(curImport)
336                 if (wildImp.exists)
337                   findRef(checkNewOrShadowed(wildImp, wildImport), wildImport, ctx)(outer)
338                 else {
339                   updateUnimported()
340                   loop(ctx)(outer)
341                 }
342               }
343               else {
344                 updateUnimported()
345                 loop(ctx)(outer)
346               }
347             }
348             else loop(ctx)(outer)
349           }
350         }
351       }
352 
353       // begin findRef
354       loop(NoContext)(ctx)
355     }
356 
357     // begin typedIdent
358     def kind = if (name.isTermName) "" else "type "
359     typr.println(s"typed ident $kind$name in ${ctx.owner}")
360     if (ctx.mode is Mode.Pattern) {
361       if (name == nme.WILDCARD)
362         return tree.withType(pt)
363       if (untpd.isVarPattern(tree) && name.isTermName)
364         return typed(desugar.patternVar(tree), pt)
365     }
366 
367     val rawType = {
368       val saved1 = unimported
369       val saved2 = foundUnderScala2
370       unimported = Set.empty
371       foundUnderScala2 = NoType
372       try {
373         var found = findRef(NoType, BindingPrec.nothingBound, NoContext)
374         if (foundUnderScala2.exists && !(foundUnderScala2 =:= found)) {
375           ctx.migrationWarning(
376             ex"""Name resolution will change.
377               | currently selected                     : $foundUnderScala2
378               | in the future, without -language:Scala2: $found""", tree.pos)
379           found = foundUnderScala2
380         }
381         found
382       }
383       finally {
384       	unimported = saved1
385       	foundUnderScala2 = saved2
386       }
387     }
388 
389     val ownType =
390       if (rawType.exists)
391         ensureAccessible(rawType, superAccess = false, tree.pos)
392       else if (name == nme._scope) {
393         // gross hack to support current xml literals.
394         // awaiting a better implicits based solution for library-supported xml
395         return ref(defn.XMLTopScopeModuleRef)
396       }
397       else if (name.toTermName == nme.ERROR)
398         UnspecifiedErrorType
399       else if (ctx.owner.isConstructor && ctx.mode.is(Mode.InSuperCall) &&
400           ctx.owner.owner.unforcedDecls.lookup(tree.name).exists) {
401         // When InSuperCall mode and in a constructor we are in the arguments
402         // of a this(...) constructor call
403         errorType(ex"$tree is not accessible from constructor arguments", tree.pos)
404       } else
405         errorType(new MissingIdent(tree, kind, name.show), tree.pos)
406 
407     val tree1 = ownType match {
408       case ownType: NamedType if !prefixIsElidable(ownType) =>
409         ref(ownType).withPos(tree.pos)
410       case _ =>
411         tree.withType(ownType)
412     }
413 
414     checkStableIdentPattern(tree1, pt)
415     checkValue(tree1, pt)
416   }
417 
418   /** Check that a stable identifier pattern is indeed stable (SLS 8.1.5)
419    */
420   private def checkStableIdentPattern(tree: Tree, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = {
421     if (ctx.mode.is(Mode.Pattern) &&
422         !tree.isType &&
423         !pt.isInstanceOf[ApplyingProto] &&
424         !tree.tpe.isStable &&
425         !isWildcardArg(tree))
426       ctx.error(s"stable identifier required, but ${tree.show} found", tree.pos)
427 
428     tree
429   }
430 
431   private def typedSelect(tree: untpd.Select, pt: Type, qual: Tree)(implicit ctx: Context): Select =
432     checkValue(assignType(cpy.Select(tree)(qual, tree.name), qual), pt)
433 
434   def typedSelect(tree: untpd.Select, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedSelect") {
435 
436     def typeSelectOnTerm(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = {
437       val qual1 = typedExpr(tree.qualifier, selectionProto(tree.name, pt, this))
438       if (tree.name.isTypeName) checkStable(qual1.tpe, qual1.pos)
439       val select = typedSelect(tree, pt, qual1)
440       if (select.tpe ne TryDynamicCallType) checkStableIdentPattern(select, pt)
441       else if (pt.isInstanceOf[PolyProto] || pt.isInstanceOf[FunProto] || pt == AssignProto) select
442       else typedDynamicSelect(tree, Nil, pt)
443     }
444 
445     def typeSelectOnType(qual: untpd.Tree)(implicit ctx: Context) =
446       typedSelect(untpd.cpy.Select(tree)(qual, tree.name.toTypeName), pt)
447 
448     def tryJavaSelectOnType(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = tree.qualifier match {
449       case Select(qual, name) => typeSelectOnType(untpd.Select(qual, name.toTypeName))
450       case Ident(name)        => typeSelectOnType(untpd.Ident(name.toTypeName))
451       case _                  => errorTree(tree, "cannot convert to type selection") // will never be printed due to fallback
452     }
453 
454     def selectWithFallback(fallBack: Context => Tree) =
455       tryAlternatively(typeSelectOnTerm(_))(fallBack)
456 
457     if (tree.qualifier.isType) {
458       val qual1 = typedType(tree.qualifier, selectionProto(tree.name, pt, this))
459       assignType(cpy.Select(tree)(qual1, tree.name), qual1)
460     }
461     else if (ctx.compilationUnit.isJava && tree.name.isTypeName)
462       // SI-3120 Java uses the same syntax, A.B, to express selection from the
463       // value A and from the type A. We have to try both.
464       selectWithFallback(tryJavaSelectOnType(_)) // !!! possibly exponential bcs of qualifier retyping
465     else if (tree.name == nme.withFilter && tree.getAttachment(desugar.MaybeFilter).isDefined)
466       selectWithFallback {
467         implicit ctx =>
468           typedSelect(untpd.cpy.Select(tree)(tree.qualifier, nme.filter), pt) // !!! possibly exponential bcs of qualifier retyping
469       }
470     else
471       typeSelectOnTerm(ctx)
472   }

474   def typedThis(tree: untpd.This)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedThis") {
475     assignType(tree)
476   }

478   def typedSuper(tree: untpd.Super, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedSuper") {
479     val qual1 = typed(tree.qual)
480     val inConstrCall = pt match {
481       case pt: SelectionProto if pt.name == nme.CONSTRUCTOR => true
482       case _ => false
483     }
484     pt match {
485       case pt: SelectionProto if pt.name.isTypeName =>
486         qual1 // don't do super references for types; they are meaningless anyway
487       case _ =>
488         assignType(cpy.Super(tree)(qual1, tree.mix), qual1, inConstrCall)
489     }
490   }

492   def typedLiteral(tree: untpd.Literal)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedLiteral") {
493     assignType(tree)
494   }
495 
496   def typedNew(tree: untpd.New, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = track("typedNew") {
497     tree.tpt match {
498       case templ: untpd.Template =>
499         import untpd._
500         var templ1 = templ
501         def isEligible(tp: Type) = tp.exists && !tp.typeSymbol.is(Final)
502         if (templ1.parents.isEmpty &&
503             isFullyDefined(pt, ForceDegree.noBottom) &&
504             isEligible(pt.underlyingClassRef(refinementOK = false)))
505           templ1 = cpy.Template(templ)(parents = untpd.TypeTree(pt) :: Nil)
506         templ1.parents foreach {
507           case parent: RefTree =>
508             typedAheadImpl(parent, tree => inferTypeParams(typedType(tree), pt))
509           case _ =>
510         }
511         val x = tpnme.ANON_CLASS
512         val clsDef = TypeDef(x, templ1).withFlags(Final)
513         typed(cpy.Block(tree)(clsDef :: Nil, New(Ident(x), Nil)), pt)
514       case _ =>
515         var tpt1 = typedType(tree.tpt)
516         tpt1 = tpt1.withType(ensureAccessible(tpt1.tpe, superAccess = false, tpt1.pos))
517         tpt1.tpe.dealias match {
518           case TypeApplications.EtaExpansion(tycon) => tpt1 = tpt1.withType(tycon)
519           case _ =>
520         }
521         checkClassType(tpt1.tpe, tpt1.pos, traitReq = false, stablePrefixReq = true)
522 
523         tpt1 match {
524           case AppliedTypeTree(_, targs) =>
525             for (targ @ TypeBoundsTree(_, _) <- targs)
526               ctx.error(WildcardOnTypeArgumentNotAllowedOnNew(), targ.pos)
527           case _ =>
528         }
529 
530         assignType(cpy.New(tree)(tpt1), tpt1)
531         // todo in a later phase: checkInstantiatable(cls, tpt1.pos)
532     }
533   }
534 
535   def typedTyped(tree: untpd.Typed, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedTyped") {
536     /*  Handles three cases:
537      *  @param  ifPat    how to handle a pattern (_: T)
538      *  @param  ifExpr   how to handle an expression (e: T)
539      *  @param  wildName what name `w` to use in the rewriting of
540      *                   (x: T) to (x @ (w: T)). This is either `_` or `_*`.
541      */
542     def cases(ifPat: => Tree, ifExpr: => Tree, wildName: TermName) = tree.expr match {
543       case id: untpd.Ident if (ctx.mode is Mode.Pattern) && untpd.isVarPattern(id) =>
544         if (id.name == nme.WILDCARD || id.name == nme.WILDCARD_STAR) ifPat
545         else {
546           import untpd._
547           typed(Bind(id.name, Typed(Ident(wildName), tree.tpt)).withPos(tree.pos), pt)
548         }
549       case _ => ifExpr
550     }
551     def ascription(tpt: Tree, isWildcard: Boolean) = {
552       val underlyingTreeTpe =
553         if (isRepeatedParamType(tpt)) TypeTree(defn.SeqType.appliedTo(pt :: Nil))
554         else tpt
555 
556       val expr1 =
557         if (isRepeatedParamType(tpt)) tree.expr.withType(defn.SeqType.appliedTo(pt :: Nil))
558         else if (isWildcard) tree.expr.withType(tpt.tpe)
559         else typed(tree.expr, tpt.tpe.widenSkolem)
560       assignType(cpy.Typed(tree)(expr1, tpt), underlyingTreeTpe)
561     }
562     if (untpd.isWildcardStarArg(tree))
563       cases(
564         ifPat = ascription(TypeTree(defn.RepeatedParamType.appliedTo(pt)), isWildcard = true),
565         ifExpr = seqToRepeated(typedExpr(tree.expr, defn.SeqType.appliedTo(defn.AnyType))),
566         wildName = nme.WILDCARD_STAR)
567     else {
568       def typedTpt = checkSimpleKinded(typedType(tree.tpt))
569       def handlePattern: Tree = {
570         val tpt1 = typedTpt
571         if (!ctx.isAfterTyper) tpt1.tpe.<:<(pt)(ctx.addMode(Mode.GADTflexible))
572         // special case for an abstract type that comes with a class tag
573         tryWithClassTag(ascription(tpt1, isWildcard = true), pt)
574       }
575       cases(
576         ifPat = handlePattern,
577         ifExpr = ascription(typedTpt, isWildcard = false),
578         wildName = nme.WILDCARD)
579     }
580   }
581 
582   /** For a typed tree `e: T`, if `T` is an abstract type for which an implicit class tag `ctag`
583    *  exists, rewrite to `ctag(e)`.
584    *  @pre We are in pattern-matching mode (Mode.Pattern)
585    */
586   def tryWithClassTag(tree: Typed, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = tree.tpt.tpe.dealias match {
587     case tref: TypeRef if !tref.symbol.isClass && !ctx.isAfterTyper =>
588       require(ctx.mode.is(Mode.Pattern))
589       inferImplicit(defn.ClassTagType.appliedTo(tref),
590                     EmptyTree, tree.tpt.pos)(ctx.retractMode(Mode.Pattern)) match {
591         case SearchSuccess(clsTag, _, _) =>
592           typed(untpd.Apply(untpd.TypedSplice(clsTag), untpd.TypedSplice(tree.expr)), pt)
593         case _ =>
594           tree
595       }
596     case _ => tree
597   }
598 
599   def typedNamedArg(tree: untpd.NamedArg, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = track("typedNamedArg") {
600     val arg1 = typed(tree.arg, pt)
601     assignType(cpy.NamedArg(tree)(tree.name, arg1), arg1)
602   }
603 
604   def typedAssign(tree: untpd.Assign, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = track("typedAssign") {
605     tree.lhs match {
606       case lhs @ Apply(fn, args) =>
607         typed(untpd.Apply(untpd.Select(fn, nme.update), args :+ tree.rhs), pt)
608       case untpd.TypedSplice(Apply(MaybePoly(Select(fn, app), targs), args)) if app == nme.apply =>
609         val rawUpdate: untpd.Tree = untpd.Select(untpd.TypedSplice(fn), nme.update)
610         val wrappedUpdate =
611           if (targs.isEmpty) rawUpdate
612           else untpd.TypeApply(rawUpdate, targs map (untpd.TypedSplice(_)))
613         val appliedUpdate =
614           untpd.Apply(wrappedUpdate, (args map (untpd.TypedSplice(_))) :+ tree.rhs)
615         typed(appliedUpdate, pt)
616       case lhs =>
617         val lhsCore = typedUnadapted(lhs, AssignProto)
618         def lhs1 = typed(untpd.TypedSplice(lhsCore))
619 
620         def reassignmentToVal =
621           errorTree(cpy.Assign(tree)(lhsCore, typed(tree.rhs, lhs1.tpe.widen)),
622             ReassignmentToVal(lhsCore.symbol.name))
623 
624         def canAssign(sym: Symbol) =
625           sym.is(Mutable, butNot = Accessor) ||
626           ctx.owner.isPrimaryConstructor && !sym.is(Method) && sym.owner == ctx.owner.owner ||
627             // allow assignments from the primary constructor to class fields
628           ctx.owner.name.is(TraitSetterName) || ctx.owner.isStaticConstructor
629 
630         lhsCore.tpe match {
631           case ref: TermRef =>
632             val lhsVal = lhsCore.denot.suchThat(!_.is(Method))
633             if (canAssign(lhsVal.symbol)) {
634               // lhsBounds: (T .. Any) as seen from lhs prefix, where T is the type of lhsVal.symbol
635               // This ensures we do the as-seen-from on T with variance -1. Test case neg/i2928.scala
636               val lhsBounds =
637                 TypeBounds.lower(lhsVal.symbol.info).asSeenFrom(ref.prefix, lhsVal.symbol.owner)
638               assignType(cpy.Assign(tree)(lhs1, typed(tree.rhs, lhsBounds.loBound)))
639             }
640             else {
641               val pre = ref.prefix
642               val setterName = ref.name.setterName
643               val setter = pre.member(setterName)
644               lhsCore match {
645                 case lhsCore: RefTree if setter.exists =>
646                   val setterTypeRaw = pre.select(setterName, setter)
647                   val setterType = ensureAccessible(setterTypeRaw, isSuperSelection(lhsCore), tree.pos)
648                   val lhs2 = untpd.rename(lhsCore, setterName).withType(setterType)
649                   typedUnadapted(untpd.Apply(untpd.TypedSplice(lhs2), tree.rhs :: Nil))
650                 case _ =>
651                   reassignmentToVal
652               }
653             }
654           case TryDynamicCallType =>
655             typedDynamicAssign(tree, pt)
656           case tpe =>
657             reassignmentToVal
658         }
659     }
660   }
661 
662   def typedBlockStats(stats: List[untpd.Tree])(implicit ctx: Context): (Context, List[tpd.Tree]) =
663     (indexAndAnnotate(stats), typedStats(stats, ctx.owner))
664 
665   def typedBlock(tree: untpd.Block, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = track("typedBlock") {
666     val (exprCtx, stats1) = typedBlockStats(tree.stats)
667     val ept = pt.notApplied
668     val expr1 = typedExpr(tree.expr, ept)(exprCtx)
669     ensureNoLocalRefs(
670       cpy.Block(tree)(stats1, expr1).withType(expr1.tpe), pt, localSyms(stats1))
671   }
672 
673   def escapingRefs(block: Tree, localSyms: => List[Symbol])(implicit ctx: Context): collection.Set[NamedType] = {
674     lazy val locals = localSyms.toSet
675     block.tpe namedPartsWith (tp => locals.contains(tp.symbol))
676   }
677 
678   /** Ensure that an expression's type can be expressed without references to locally defined
679    *  symbols. This is done by adding a type ascription of a widened type that does
680    *  not refer to the locally defined symbols. The widened type is computed using
681    *  `TyperAssigner#avoid`. However, if the expected type is fully defined and not
682    *  a supertype of the widened type, we ascribe with the expected type instead.
683    *
684    *  There's a special case having to do with anonymous classes. Sometimes the
685    *  expected type of a block is the anonymous class defined inside it. In that
686    *  case there's technically a leak which is not removed by the ascription.
687    */
688   protected def ensureNoLocalRefs(tree: Tree, pt: Type, localSyms: => List[Symbol])(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = {
689     def ascribeType(tree: Tree, pt: Type): Tree = tree match {
690       case block @ Block(stats, expr) =>
691         val expr1 = ascribeType(expr, pt)
692         cpy.Block(block)(stats, expr1) withType expr1.tpe // no assignType here because avoid is redundant
693       case _ =>
694         Typed(tree, TypeTree(pt.simplified))
695     }
696     def noLeaks(t: Tree): Boolean = escapingRefs(t, localSyms).isEmpty
697     if (noLeaks(tree)) tree
698     else {
699       fullyDefinedType(tree.tpe, "block", tree.pos)
700       var avoidingType = avoid(tree.tpe, localSyms)
701       val ptDefined = isFullyDefined(pt, ForceDegree.none)
702       if (ptDefined && !(avoidingType <:< pt)) avoidingType = pt
703       val tree1 = ascribeType(tree, avoidingType)
704       assert(ptDefined || noLeaks(tree1) || tree1.tpe.widen.isErroneous,
705           // `ptDefined` needed because of special case of anonymous classes
706           i"leak: ${escapingRefs(tree1, localSyms).toList}%, % in $tree1")
707       tree1
708     }
709   }
710 
711   def typedIf(tree: untpd.If, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedIf") {
712     val cond1 = typed(tree.cond, defn.BooleanType)
713     val thenp2 :: elsep2 :: Nil = harmonic(harmonize) {
714       val thenp1 = typed(tree.thenp, pt.notApplied)
715       val elsep1 = typed(tree.elsep orElse (untpd.unitLiteral withPos tree.pos), pt.notApplied)
716       thenp1 :: elsep1 :: Nil
717     }
718     assignType(cpy.If(tree)(cond1, thenp2, elsep2), thenp2, elsep2)
719   }
720 
721   /** Decompose function prototype into a list of parameter prototypes and a result prototype
722    *  tree, using WildcardTypes where a type is not known.
723    *  For the result type we do this even if the expected type is not fully
724    *  defined, which is a bit of a hack. But it's needed to make the following work
725    *  (see typers.scala and printers/PlainPrinter.scala for examples).
726    *
727    *     def double(x: Char): String = s"$x$x"
728    *     "abc" flatMap double
729    */
730   private def decomposeProtoFunction(pt: Type, defaultArity: Int)(implicit ctx: Context): (List[Type], untpd.Tree) = {
731     def typeTree(tp: Type) = tp match {
732       case _: WildcardType => untpd.TypeTree()
733       case _ => untpd.TypeTree(tp)
734     }
735     pt.stripTypeVar match {
736       case _ if defn.isNonDepFunctionType(pt) =>
737         // if expected parameter type(s) are wildcards, approximate from below.
738         // if expected result type is a wildcard, approximate from above.
739         // this can type the greatest set of admissible closures.
740         val funType = pt.dealias
741         (funType.argTypesLo.init, typeTree(funType.argTypesHi.last))
742       case SAMType(meth) =>
743         val mt @ MethodTpe(_, formals, restpe) = meth.info
744         (formals,
745          if (mt.isDependent)
746            untpd.DependentTypeTree(syms => restpe.substParams(mt, syms.map(_.termRef)))
747          else
748            typeTree(restpe))
749       case tp: TypeParamRef =>
750         decomposeProtoFunction(ctx.typerState.constraint.entry(tp).bounds.hi, defaultArity)
751       case _ =>
752         (List.tabulate(defaultArity)(alwaysWildcardType), untpd.TypeTree())
753     }
754   }
755 
756   def typedFunction(tree: untpd.Function, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = track("typedFunction") {
757     if (ctx.mode is Mode.Type) typedFunctionType(tree, pt)
758     else typedFunctionValue(tree, pt)
759   }
760 
761   def typedFunctionType(tree: untpd.Function, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = {
762     val untpd.Function(args, body) = tree
763     val isImplicit = tree match {
764       case _: untpd.ImplicitFunction =>
765         if (args.length == 0) {
766           ctx.error(ImplicitFunctionTypeNeedsNonEmptyParameterList(), tree.pos)
767           false
768         }
769         else true
770       case _ => false
771     }
772     val funCls = defn.FunctionClass(args.length, isImplicit)
773 
774     /** Typechecks dependent function type with given parameters `params` */
775     def typedDependent(params: List[ValDef])(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = {
776       completeParams(params)
777       val params1 = params.map(typedExpr(_).asInstanceOf[ValDef])
778       val resultTpt = typed(body)
779       val companion = if (isImplicit) ImplicitMethodType else MethodType
780       val mt = companion.fromSymbols(params1.map(_.symbol), resultTpt.tpe)
781       if (mt.isParamDependent)
782         ctx.error(i"$mt is an illegal function type because it has inter-parameter dependencies", tree.pos)
783       val resTpt = TypeTree(mt.nonDependentResultApprox).withPos(body.pos)
784       val typeArgs = params1.map(_.tpt) :+ resTpt
785       val tycon = TypeTree(funCls.typeRef)
786       val core = assignType(cpy.AppliedTypeTree(tree)(tycon, typeArgs), tycon, typeArgs)
787       val appMeth = ctx.newSymbol(ctx.owner, nme.apply, Synthetic | Deferred, mt)
788       val appDef = assignType(
789         untpd.DefDef(appMeth.name, Nil, List(params1), resultTpt, EmptyTree),
790         appMeth)
791       RefinedTypeTree(core, List(appDef), ctx.owner.asClass)
792     }
793 
794     args match {
795       case ValDef(_, _, _) :: _ =>
796         typedDependent(args.asInstanceOf[List[ValDef]])(
797           ctx.fresh.setOwner(ctx.newRefinedClassSymbol(tree.pos)).setNewScope)
798       case _ =>
799         typed(cpy.AppliedTypeTree(tree)(untpd.TypeTree(funCls.typeRef), args :+ body), pt)
800     }
801   }
802 
803   def typedFunctionValue(tree: untpd.Function, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = {
804     val untpd.Function(params: List[untpd.ValDef] @unchecked, body) = tree
805 
806     pt match {
807       case pt: TypeVar if untpd.isFunctionWithUnknownParamType(tree) =>
808         // try to instantiate `pt` if this is possible. If it does not
809         // work the error will be reported later in `inferredParam`,
810         // when we try to infer the parameter type.
811         isFullyDefined(pt, ForceDegree.noBottom)
812       case _ =>
813     }
814 
815     val (protoFormals, resultTpt) = decomposeProtoFunction(pt, params.length)
816 
817     def refersTo(arg: untpd.Tree, param: untpd.ValDef): Boolean = arg match {
818       case Ident(name) => name == param.name
819       case _ => false
820     }
821 
822     /** The function body to be returned in the closure. Can become a TypedSplice
823       *  of a typed expression if this is necessary to infer a parameter type.
824       */
825     var fnBody = tree.body
826 
827     /** A map from parameter names to unique positions where the parameter
828       *  appears in the argument list of an application.
829       */
830     var paramIndex = Map[Name, Int]()
831 
832     /** If parameter `param` appears exactly once as an argument in `args`,
833       *  the singleton list consisting of its position in `args`, otherwise `Nil`.
834       */
835     def paramIndices(param: untpd.ValDef, args: List[untpd.Tree]): List[Int] = {
836       def loop(args: List[untpd.Tree], start: Int): List[Int] = args match {
837         case arg :: args1 =>
838           val others = loop(args1, start + 1)
839           if (refersTo(arg, param)) start :: others else others
840         case _ => Nil
841       }
842       val allIndices = loop(args, 0)
843       if (allIndices.length == 1) allIndices else Nil
844     }
845 
846     /** If function is of the form
847       *      (x1, ..., xN) => f(... x1, ..., XN, ...)
848       *  where each `xi` occurs exactly once in the argument list of `f` (in
849       *  any order), the type of `f`, otherwise NoType.
850       *  Updates `fnBody` and `paramIndex` as a side effect.
851       *  @post: If result exists, `paramIndex` is defined for the name of
852       *         every parameter in `params`.
853       */
854     def calleeType: Type = fnBody match {
855       case Apply(expr, args) =>
856         paramIndex = {
857           for (param <- params; idx <- paramIndices(param, args))
858           yield param.name -> idx
859         }.toMap
860         if (paramIndex.size == params.length)
861           expr match {
862             case untpd.TypedSplice(expr1) =>
863               expr1.tpe
864             case _ =>
865               val protoArgs = args map (_ withType WildcardType)
866               val callProto = FunProto(protoArgs, WildcardType, this)
867               val expr1 = typedExpr(expr, callProto)
868               fnBody = cpy.Apply(fnBody)(untpd.TypedSplice(expr1), args)
869               expr1.tpe
870           }
871         else NoType
872       case _ =>
873         NoType
874     }
875 
876     /** Two attempts: First, if expected type is fully defined pick this one.
877       *  Second, if function is of the form
878       *      (x1, ..., xN) => f(... x1, ..., XN, ...)
879       *  where each `xi` occurs exactly once in the argument list of `f` (in
880       *  any order), and f has a method type MT, pick the corresponding parameter
881       *  type in MT, if this one is fully defined.
882       *  If both attempts fail, issue a "missing parameter type" error.
883       */
884     def inferredParamType(param: untpd.ValDef, formal: Type): Type = {
885       if (isFullyDefined(formal, ForceDegree.noBottom)) return formal
886       calleeType.widen match {
887         case mtpe: MethodType =>
888           val pos = paramIndex(param.name)
889           if (pos < mtpe.paramInfos.length) {
890             val ptype = mtpe.paramInfos(pos)
891             if (isFullyDefined(ptype, ForceDegree.noBottom) && !ptype.isRepeatedParam)
892               return ptype
893           }
894         case _ =>
895       }
896       errorType(AnonymousFunctionMissingParamType(param, params, tree, pt), param.pos)
897     }
898 
899     def protoFormal(i: Int): Type =
900       if (protoFormals.length == params.length) protoFormals(i)
901       else errorType(WrongNumberOfParameters(protoFormals.length), tree.pos)
902 
903     /** Is `formal` a product type which is elementwise compatible with `params`? */
904     def ptIsCorrectProduct(formal: Type) = {
905       isFullyDefined(formal, ForceDegree.noBottom) &&
906       defn.isProductSubType(formal) &&
907       Applications.productSelectorTypes(formal).corresponds(params) {
908         (argType, param) =>
909           param.tpt.isEmpty || argType <:< typedAheadType(param.tpt).tpe
910       }
911     }
912 
913     val desugared =
914       if (protoFormals.length == 1 && params.length != 1 && ptIsCorrectProduct(protoFormals.head)) {
915         desugar.makeTupledFunction(params, fnBody)
916       }
917       else {
918         val inferredParams: List[untpd.ValDef] =
919           for ((param, i) <- params.zipWithIndex) yield
920             if (!param.tpt.isEmpty) param
921             else cpy.ValDef(param)(
922               tpt = untpd.TypeTree(
923                 inferredParamType(param, protoFormal(i)).underlyingIfRepeated(isJava = false)))
924         val inlineable = pt.hasAnnotation(defn.InlineParamAnnot)
925         desugar.makeClosure(inferredParams, fnBody, resultTpt, inlineable)
926       }
927     typed(desugared, pt)
928   }
929 
930   def typedClosure(tree: untpd.Closure, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedClosure") {
931     val env1 = tree.env mapconserve (typed(_))
932     val meth1 = typedUnadapted(tree.meth)
933     val target =
934       if (tree.tpt.isEmpty)
935         meth1.tpe.widen match {
936           case mt: MethodType =>
937             pt match {
938               case SAMType(meth)
939               if !defn.isFunctionType(pt) && mt <:< meth.info =>
940                 if (!isFullyDefined(pt, ForceDegree.all))
941                   ctx.error(ex"result type of closure is an underspecified SAM type $pt", tree.pos)
942                 TypeTree(pt)
943               case _ =>
944                 if (!mt.isParamDependent) EmptyTree
945                 else throw new java.lang.Error(
946                   i"""internal error: cannot turn method type $mt into closure
947                      |because it has internal parameter dependencies,
948                      |position = ${tree.pos}, raw type = ${mt.toString}""") // !!! DEBUG. Eventually, convert to an error?
949             }
950           case tp =>
951             throw new java.lang.Error(i"internal error: closing over non-method $tp, pos = ${tree.pos}")
952         }
953       else typed(tree.tpt)
954     //println(i"typing closure $tree : ${meth1.tpe.widen}")
955     assignType(cpy.Closure(tree)(env1, meth1, target), meth1, target)
956   }
957 
958   def typedMatch(tree: untpd.Match, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = track("typedMatch") {
959     tree.selector match {
960       case EmptyTree =>
961         val (protoFormals, _) = decomposeProtoFunction(pt, 1)
962         val unchecked = pt.isRef(defn.PartialFunctionClass)
963         typed(desugar.makeCaseLambda(tree.cases, protoFormals.length, unchecked) withPos tree.pos, pt)
964       case _ =>
965         val sel1 = typedExpr(tree.selector)
966         val selType = fullyDefinedType(sel1.tpe, "pattern selector", tree.pos).widen
967 
968         val cases1 = harmonic(harmonize)(typedCases(tree.cases, selType, pt.notApplied))
969           .asInstanceOf[List[CaseDef]]
970         assignType(cpy.Match(tree)(sel1, cases1), cases1)
971     }
972   }
973 
974   def typedCases(cases: List[untpd.CaseDef], selType: Type, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = {
975 
976     /** gadtSyms = "all type parameters of enclosing methods that appear
977      *              non-variantly in the selector type" todo: should typevars
978      *              which appear with variances +1 and -1 (in different
979      *              places) be considered as well?
980      */
981     val gadtSyms: Set[Symbol] = trace(i"GADT syms of $selType", gadts) {
982       val accu = new TypeAccumulator[Set[Symbol]] {
983         def apply(tsyms: Set[Symbol], t: Type): Set[Symbol] = {
984           val tsyms1 = t match {
985             case tr: TypeRef if (tr.symbol is TypeParam) && tr.symbol.owner.isTerm && variance == 0 =>
986               tsyms + tr.symbol
987             case _ =>
988               tsyms
989           }
990           foldOver(tsyms1, t)
991         }
992       }
993       accu(Set.empty, selType)
994     }
995 
996     cases mapconserve (typedCase(_, pt, selType, gadtSyms))
997   }
998 
999   /** Type a case. Overridden in ReTyper, that's why it's separate from
1000    *  typedCases.
1001    */
1002   def typedCase(tree: untpd.CaseDef, pt: Type, selType: Type, gadtSyms: Set[Symbol])(implicit ctx: Context): CaseDef = track("typedCase") {
1003     val originalCtx = ctx
1004 
1005     val gadtCtx = ctx.fresh.setFreshGADTBounds
1006     for (sym <- gadtSyms)
1007       if (!gadtCtx.gadt.bounds.contains(sym))
1008         gadtCtx.gadt.setBounds(sym, TypeBounds.empty)
1009 
1010     /** - strip all instantiated TypeVars from pattern types.
1011      *    run/reducable.scala is a test case that shows stripping typevars is necessary.
1012      *  - enter all symbols introduced by a Bind in current scope
1013      */
1014     val indexPattern = new TreeMap {
1015       val stripTypeVars = new TypeMap {
1016         def apply(t: Type) = mapOver(t)
1017       }
1018       override def transform(trt: Tree)(implicit ctx: Context) =
1019         super.transform(trt.withType(stripTypeVars(trt.tpe))) match {
1020           case b: Bind =>
1021             val sym = b.symbol
1022             if (sym.name != tpnme.WILDCARD)
1023               if (ctx.scope.lookup(b.name) == NoSymbol) ctx.enter(sym)
1024               else ctx.error(new DuplicateBind(b, tree), b.pos)
1025             if (!ctx.isAfterTyper) {
1026               val bounds = ctx.gadt.bounds(sym)
1027               if (bounds != null) sym.info = bounds
1028             }
1029             b
1030           case t => t
1031         }
1032       }
1033 
1034     def caseRest(pat: Tree)(implicit ctx: Context) = {
1035       val pat1 = indexPattern.transform(pat)
1036       val guard1 = typedExpr(tree.guard, defn.BooleanType)
1037       var body1 = ensureNoLocalRefs(typedExpr(tree.body, pt), pt, ctx.scope.toList)
1038       if (pt.isValueType) // insert a cast if body does not conform to expected type if we disregard gadt bounds
1039         body1 = body1.ensureConforms(pt)(originalCtx)
1040       assignType(cpy.CaseDef(tree)(pat1, guard1, body1), body1)
1041     }
1042 
1043     val pat1 = typedPattern(tree.pat, selType)(gadtCtx)
1044     caseRest(pat1)(gadtCtx.fresh.setNewScope)
1045   }
1046 
1047   def typedReturn(tree: untpd.Return)(implicit ctx: Context): Return = track("typedReturn") {
1048     def returnProto(owner: Symbol, locals: Scope): Type =
1049       if (owner.isConstructor) defn.UnitType
1050       else owner.info match {
1051         case info: PolyType =>
1052           val tparams = locals.toList.takeWhile(_ is TypeParam)
1053           assert(info.paramNames.length == tparams.length,
1054                  i"return mismatch from $owner, tparams = $tparams, locals = ${locals.toList}%, %")
1055           info.instantiate(tparams.map(_.typeRef)).finalResultType
1056         case info =>
1057           info.finalResultType
1058       }
1059     def enclMethInfo(cx: Context): (Tree, Type) = {
1060       val owner = cx.owner
1061       if (owner.isType) {
1062         ctx.error(ReturnOutsideMethodDefinition(owner), tree.pos)
1063         (EmptyTree, WildcardType)
1064       }
1065       else if (owner != cx.outer.owner && owner.isRealMethod) {
1066         if (owner.isInlineMethod)
1067           (EmptyTree, errorType(NoReturnFromInline(owner), tree.pos))
1068         else if (!owner.isCompleted)
1069           (EmptyTree, errorType(MissingReturnTypeWithReturnStatement(owner), tree.pos))
1070         else {
1071           val from = Ident(TermRef(NoPrefix, owner.asTerm))
1072           val proto = returnProto(owner, cx.scope)
1073           (from, proto)
1074         }
1075       }
1076       else enclMethInfo(cx.outer)
1077     }
1078     val (from, proto) =
1079       if (tree.from.isEmpty) enclMethInfo(ctx)
1080       else {
1081         val from = tree.from.asInstanceOf[tpd.Tree]
1082         val proto =
1083           if (ctx.erasedTypes) from.symbol.info.finalResultType
1084           else WildcardType // We cannot reliably detect the internal type view of polymorphic or dependent methods
1085                             // because we do not know the internal type params and method params.
1086                             // Hence no adaptation is possible, and we assume WildcardType as prototype.
1087         (from, proto)
1088       }
1089     val expr1 = typedExpr(tree.expr orElse untpd.unitLiteral.withPos(tree.pos), proto)
1090     assignType(cpy.Return(tree)(expr1, from))
1091   }
1092 
1093   def typedTry(tree: untpd.Try, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Try = track("typedTry") {
1094     val expr2 :: cases2x = harmonic(harmonize) {
1095       val expr1 = typed(tree.expr, pt.notApplied)
1096       val cases1 = typedCases(tree.cases, defn.ThrowableType, pt.notApplied)
1097       expr1 :: cases1
1098     }
1099     val finalizer1 = typed(tree.finalizer, defn.UnitType)
1100     val cases2 = cases2x.asInstanceOf[List[CaseDef]]
1101     assignType(cpy.Try(tree)(expr2, cases2, finalizer1), expr2, cases2)
1102   }
1103 
1104   def typedThrow(tree: untpd.Throw)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedThrow") {
1105     val expr1 = typed(tree.expr, defn.ThrowableType)
1106     Throw(expr1).withPos(tree.pos)
1107   }

1109   def typedQuote(tree: untpd.Quote, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedQuote") {
1110     val untpd.Quote(body) = tree
1111     val isType = body.isType
1112     val resultClass = if (isType) defn.QuotedTypeClass else defn.QuotedExprClass
1113     val proto1 = pt.baseType(resultClass) match {
1114       case AppliedType(_, argType :: Nil) => argType
1115       case _ => WildcardType
1116     }
1117     val nestedCtx = ctx.fresh.setTree(tree)
1118     if (isType) {
1119       val body1 = typedType(body, proto1)(nestedCtx)
1120       ref(defn.typeQuoteMethod).appliedToTypeTrees(body1 :: Nil)
1121     }
1122     else {
1123       val body1 = typed(body, proto1)(nestedCtx)
1124       ref(defn.quoteMethod).appliedToType(body1.tpe.widen).appliedTo(body1)
1125     }
1126   }

1128   def typedSeqLiteral(tree: untpd.SeqLiteral, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): SeqLiteral = track("typedSeqLiteral") {
1129     val proto1 = pt.elemType match {
1130       case NoType => WildcardType
1131       case bounds: TypeBounds => WildcardType(bounds)
1132       case elemtp => elemtp
1133     }
1134     val elems1 = tree.elems mapconserve (typed(_, proto1))
1135     val proto2 = // the computed type of the `elemtpt` field
1136       if (!tree.elemtpt.isEmpty) WildcardType
1137       else if (isFullyDefined(proto1, ForceDegree.none)) proto1
1138       else if (tree.elems.isEmpty && tree.isInstanceOf[Trees.JavaSeqLiteral[_]])
1139         defn.ObjectType // generic empty Java varargs are of type Object[]
1140       else ctx.typeComparer.lub(elems1.tpes)
1141     val elemtpt1 = typed(tree.elemtpt, proto2)
1142     assignType(cpy.SeqLiteral(tree)(elems1, elemtpt1), elems1, elemtpt1)
1143   }

1145   def typedInlined(tree: untpd.Inlined, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Inlined = {
1146     val (exprCtx, bindings1) = typedBlockStats(tree.bindings)
1147     val expansion1 = typed(tree.expansion, pt)(inlineContext(tree.call)(exprCtx))
1148     assignType(cpy.Inlined(tree)(tree.call, bindings1.asInstanceOf[List[MemberDef]], expansion1),
1149         bindings1, expansion1)
1150   }

1152   def typedTypeTree(tree: untpd.TypeTree, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedTypeTree") {
1153     tree match {
1154       case tree: untpd.DerivedTypeTree =>
1155         tree.ensureCompletions
1156         tree.getAttachment(untpd.OriginalSymbol) match {
1157           case Some(origSym) =>
1158             TypeTree(tree.derivedType(origSym)).withPos(tree.pos)
1159             // btw, no need to remove the attachment. The typed
1160             // tree is different from the untyped one, so the
1161             // untyped tree is no longer accessed after all
1162             // accesses with typedTypeTree are done.
1163           case None =>
1164             errorTree(tree, "Something's wrong: missing original symbol for type tree")
1165         }
1166       case _ =>
1167         tree.withType(
1168           if (isFullyDefined(pt, ForceDegree.none)) pt else UnspecifiedErrorType)
1169     }
1170   }

1172   def typedSingletonTypeTree(tree: untpd.SingletonTypeTree)(implicit ctx: Context): SingletonTypeTree = track("typedSingletonTypeTree") {
1173     val ref1 = typedExpr(tree.ref)
1174     checkStable(ref1.tpe, tree.pos)
1175     assignType(cpy.SingletonTypeTree(tree)(ref1), ref1)
1176   }

1178   def typedAndTypeTree(tree: untpd.AndTypeTree)(implicit ctx: Context): AndTypeTree = track("typedAndTypeTree") {
1179     val left1 = checkSimpleKinded(typed(tree.left))
1180     val right1 = checkSimpleKinded(typed(tree.right))
1181     assignType(cpy.AndTypeTree(tree)(left1, right1), left1, right1)
1182   }

1184   def typedOrTypeTree(tree: untpd.OrTypeTree)(implicit ctx: Context): OrTypeTree = track("typedOrTypeTree") {
1185     val where = "in a union type"
1186     val left1 = checkNotSingleton(checkSimpleKinded(typed(tree.left)), where)
1187     val right1 = checkNotSingleton(checkSimpleKinded(typed(tree.right)), where)
1188     assignType(cpy.OrTypeTree(tree)(left1, right1), left1, right1)
1189   }

1191   def typedRefinedTypeTree(tree: untpd.RefinedTypeTree)(implicit ctx: Context): RefinedTypeTree = track("typedRefinedTypeTree") {
1192     val tpt1 = if (tree.tpt.isEmpty) TypeTree(defn.ObjectType) else typedAheadType(tree.tpt)
1193     val refineClsDef = desugar.refinedTypeToClass(tpt1, tree.refinements).withPos(tree.pos)
1194     val refineCls = createSymbol(refineClsDef).asClass
1195     val TypeDef(_, impl: Template) = typed(refineClsDef)
1196     val refinements1 = impl.body
1197     assert(tree.refinements.length == refinements1.length, s"${tree.refinements} != $refinements1")
1198     val seen = mutable.Set[Symbol]()
1199     for (refinement <- refinements1) { // TODO: get clarity whether we want to enforce these conditions
1200       typr.println(s"adding refinement $refinement")
1201       checkRefinementNonCyclic(refinement, refineCls, seen)
1202       val rsym = refinement.symbol
1203       if (rsym.info.isInstanceOf[PolyType] && rsym.allOverriddenSymbols.isEmpty)
1204         ctx.error(PolymorphicMethodMissingTypeInParent(rsym, tpt1.symbol), refinement.pos)
1205     }
1206     assignType(cpy.RefinedTypeTree(tree)(tpt1, refinements1), tpt1, refinements1, refineCls)
1207   }
1208 
1209   def typedAppliedTypeTree(tree: untpd.AppliedTypeTree)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedAppliedTypeTree") {
1210     val tpt1 = typed(tree.tpt, AnyTypeConstructorProto)(ctx.retractMode(Mode.Pattern))
1211     val tparams = tpt1.tpe.typeParams
1212     if (tparams.isEmpty) {
1213       ctx.error(TypeDoesNotTakeParameters(tpt1.tpe, tree.args), tree.pos)
1214       tpt1
1215     }
1216     else {
1217       var args = tree.args
1218       val args1 = {
1219         if (args.length != tparams.length) {
1220           wrongNumberOfTypeArgs(tpt1.tpe, tparams, args, tree.pos)
1221           args = args.take(tparams.length)
1222         }
1223         def typedArg(arg: untpd.Tree, tparam: ParamInfo) = {
1224           val (desugaredArg, argPt) =
1225             if (ctx.mode is Mode.Pattern)
1226               (if (untpd.isVarPattern(arg)) desugar.patternVar(arg) else arg, tparam.paramInfo)
1227             else
1228               (arg, WildcardType)
1229           if (tpt1.symbol.isClass)
1230             tparam match {
1231               case tparam: Symbol =>
1232                 tparam.ensureCompleted() // This is needed to get the test `compileParSetSubset` to work
1233               case _ =>
1234             }
1235           if (desugaredArg.isType) typed(desugaredArg, argPt)
1236           else desugaredArg.withType(UnspecifiedErrorType)
1237         }
1238         args.zipWithConserve(tparams)(typedArg(_, _)).asInstanceOf[List[Tree]]
1239       }
1240       val paramBounds = (tparams, args).zipped.map {
1241         case (tparam, TypeBoundsTree(EmptyTree, EmptyTree)) =>
1242           // if type argument is a wildcard, suppress kind checking since
1243           // there is no real argument.
1244           NoType
1245         case (tparam, _) =>
1246           tparam.paramInfo.bounds
1247       }
1248       val args2 = preCheckKinds(args1, paramBounds)
1249       // check that arguments conform to bounds is done in phase PostTyper
1250       assignType(cpy.AppliedTypeTree(tree)(tpt1, args2), tpt1, args2)
1251     }
1252   }
1253 
1254   def typedLambdaTypeTree(tree: untpd.LambdaTypeTree)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedLambdaTypeTree") {
1255     val LambdaTypeTree(tparams, body) = tree
1256     indexAndAnnotate(tparams)
1257     val tparams1 = tparams.mapconserve(typed(_).asInstanceOf[TypeDef])
1258     val body1 = typedType(tree.body)
1259     assignType(cpy.LambdaTypeTree(tree)(tparams1, body1), tparams1, body1)
1260   }

1262   def typedByNameTypeTree(tree: untpd.ByNameTypeTree)(implicit ctx: Context): ByNameTypeTree = track("typedByNameTypeTree") {
1263     val result1 = typed(tree.result)
1264     assignType(cpy.ByNameTypeTree(tree)(result1), result1)
1265   }

1267   def typedTypeBoundsTree(tree: untpd.TypeBoundsTree, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedTypeBoundsTree") {
1268     val TypeBoundsTree(lo, hi) = tree
1269     val lo1 = typed(lo)
1270     val hi1 = typed(hi)
1271 
1272     val lo2 = if (lo1.isEmpty) typed(untpd.TypeTree(hi1.typeOpt.bottomType)) else lo1
1273     val hi2 = if (hi1.isEmpty) typed(untpd.TypeTree(lo1.typeOpt.topType)) else hi1
1274 
1275     val tree1 = assignType(cpy.TypeBoundsTree(tree)(lo2, hi2), lo2, hi2)
1276     if (ctx.mode.is(Mode.Pattern)) {
1277       // Associate a pattern-bound type symbol with the wildcard.
1278       // The bounds of the type symbol can be constrained when comparing a pattern type
1279       // with an expected type in typedTyped. The type symbol and the defining Bind node
1280       // are eliminated once the enclosing pattern has been typechecked; see `indexPattern`
1281       // in `typedCase`.
1282       //val ptt = if (lo.isEmpty && hi.isEmpty) pt else
1283       if (ctx.isAfterTyper) tree1
1284       else {
1285         val wildcardSym = ctx.newPatternBoundSymbol(tpnme.WILDCARD, tree1.tpe & pt, tree.pos)
1286         untpd.Bind(tpnme.WILDCARD, tree1).withType(wildcardSym.typeRef)
1287       }
1288     }
1289     else tree1
1290   }
1291 
1292   def typedBind(tree: untpd.Bind, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedBind") {
1293     val pt1 = fullyDefinedType(pt, "pattern variable", tree.pos)
1294     val body1 = typed(tree.body, pt1)
1295     body1 match {
1296       case UnApply(fn, Nil, arg :: Nil)
1297       if fn.symbol.exists && fn.symbol.owner == defn.ClassTagClass && !body1.tpe.isError =>
1298         // A typed pattern `x @ (e: T)` with an implicit `ctag: ClassTag[T]`
1299         // was rewritten to `x @ ctag(e)` by `tryWithClassTag`.
1300         // Rewrite further to `ctag(x @ e)`
1301         tpd.cpy.UnApply(body1)(fn, Nil,
1302             typed(untpd.Bind(tree.name, untpd.TypedSplice(arg)).withPos(tree.pos), arg.tpe) :: Nil)
1303       case _ =>
1304         if (tree.name == nme.WILDCARD) body1
1305         else {
1306           val sym = ctx.newPatternBoundSymbol(tree.name, body1.tpe.underlyingIfRepeated(isJava = false), tree.pos)
1307           if (ctx.mode.is(Mode.InPatternAlternative))
1308             ctx.error(i"Illegal variable ${sym.name} in pattern alternative", tree.pos)
1309           assignType(cpy.Bind(tree)(tree.name, body1), sym)
1310         }
1311     }
1312   }
1313 
1314   def typedAlternative(tree: untpd.Alternative, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Alternative = track("typedAlternative") {
1315     val nestedCtx = ctx.addMode(Mode.InPatternAlternative)
1316     val trees1 = tree.trees.mapconserve(typed(_, pt)(nestedCtx))
1317     assignType(cpy.Alternative(tree)(trees1), trees1)
1318   }

1320   def completeAnnotations(mdef: untpd.MemberDef, sym: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit = {
1321     // necessary to force annotation trees to be computed.
1322     sym.annotations.foreach(_.ensureCompleted)
1323     lazy val annotCtx = {
1324       val c = ctx.outersIterator.dropWhile(_.owner == sym).next()
1325       c.property(ExprOwner) match {
1326         case Some(exprOwner) if c.owner.isClass =>
1327           // We need to evaluate annotation arguments in an expression context, since
1328           // classes defined in a such arguments should not be entered into the
1329           // enclosing class.
1330           c.exprContext(mdef, exprOwner)
1331         case _ => c
1332       }
1333     }
1334     // necessary in order to mark the typed ahead annotations as definitely typed:
1335     untpd.modsDeco(mdef).mods.annotations.foreach(typedAnnotation(_)(annotCtx))
1336   }
1337 
1338   def typedAnnotation(annot: untpd.Tree)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedAnnotation") {
1339     typed(annot, defn.AnnotationType)
1340   }
1341 
1342   def typedValDef(vdef: untpd.ValDef, sym: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context) = track("typedValDef") {
1343     val ValDef(name, tpt, _) = vdef
1344     completeAnnotations(vdef, sym)
1345     val tpt1 = checkSimpleKinded(typedType(tpt))
1346     val rhs1 = vdef.rhs match {
1347       case rhs @ Ident(nme.WILDCARD) => rhs withType tpt1.tpe
1348       case rhs => typedExpr(rhs, tpt1.tpe)
1349     }
1350     val vdef1 = assignType(cpy.ValDef(vdef)(name, tpt1, rhs1), sym)
1351     if (sym.is(Inline, butNot = DeferredOrTermParamOrAccessor))
1352       checkInlineConformant(rhs1, em"right-hand side of inline $sym")
1353     patchIfLazy(vdef1)
1354     patchFinalVals(vdef1)
1355     vdef1
1356   }
1357 
1358   /** Add a @volitile to lazy vals when rewriting from Scala2 */
1359   private def patchIfLazy(vdef: ValDef)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit = {
1360     val sym = vdef.symbol
1361     if (sym.is(Lazy, butNot = Deferred | Module | Synthetic) && !sym.isVolatile &&
1362         ctx.scala2Mode && ctx.settings.rewrite.value.isDefined &&
1363         !ctx.isAfterTyper)
1364       patch(Position(toUntyped(vdef).pos.start), "@volatile ")
1365   }
1366 
1367   /** Adds inline to final vals with idempotent rhs
1368    *
1369    *  duplicating scalac behavior: for final vals that have rhs as constant, we do not create a field
1370    *  and instead return the value. This seemingly minor optimization has huge effect on initialization
1371    *  order and the values that can be observed during superconstructor call
1372    *
1373    *  see remark about idempotency in PostTyper#normalizeTree
1374    */
1375   private def patchFinalVals(vdef: ValDef)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit = {
1376     def isFinalInlinableVal(sym: Symbol): Boolean = {
1377       sym.is(Final, butNot = Mutable) &&
1378       isIdempotentExpr(vdef.rhs) /* &&
1379       ctx.scala2Mode (stay compatible with Scala2 for now) */
1380     }
1381     val sym = vdef.symbol
1382     sym.info match {
1383       case info: ConstantType if isFinalInlinableVal(sym) && !ctx.settings.YnoInline.value => sym.setFlag(Inline)
1384       case _ =>
1385     }
1386   }
1387 
1388   def typedDefDef(ddef: untpd.DefDef, sym: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context) = track("typedDefDef") {
1389     val DefDef(name, tparams, vparamss, tpt, _) = ddef
1390     completeAnnotations(ddef, sym)
1391     val tparams1 = tparams mapconserve (typed(_).asInstanceOf[TypeDef])
1392     val vparamss1 = vparamss nestedMapconserve (typed(_).asInstanceOf[ValDef])
1393     vparamss1.foreach(checkNoForwardDependencies)
1394     if (sym is Implicit) checkImplicitParamsNotSingletons(vparamss1)
1395     val tpt1 = checkSimpleKinded(typedType(tpt))
1396 
1397     var rhsCtx = ctx
1398     if (sym.isConstructor && !sym.isPrimaryConstructor && tparams1.nonEmpty) {
1399       // for secondary constructors we need a context that "knows"
1400       // that their type parameters are aliases of the class type parameters.
1401       // See pos/i941.scala
1402       rhsCtx = ctx.fresh.setFreshGADTBounds
1403       (tparams1, sym.owner.typeParams).zipped.foreach ((tdef, tparam) =>
1404         rhsCtx.gadt.setBounds(tdef.symbol, TypeAlias(tparam.typeRef)))
1405     }
1406     val rhs1 = typedExpr(ddef.rhs, tpt1.tpe)(rhsCtx)
1407 
1408     // Overwrite inline body to make sure it is not evaluated twice
1409     if (sym.isInlineMethod) Inliner.registerInlineInfo(sym, _ => rhs1)
1410 
1411     assignType(cpy.DefDef(ddef)(name, tparams1, vparamss1, tpt1, rhs1), sym)
1412     //todo: make sure dependent method types do not depend on implicits or by-name params
1413   }
1414 
1415   def typedTypeDef(tdef: untpd.TypeDef, sym: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedTypeDef") {
1416     val TypeDef(name, rhs) = tdef
1417     completeAnnotations(tdef, sym)
1418     val rhs1 = tdef.rhs match {
1419       case rhs @ LambdaTypeTree(tparams, body) =>
1420         val tparams1 = tparams.map(typed(_)).asInstanceOf[List[TypeDef]]
1421         val body1 = typedType(body)
1422         assignType(cpy.LambdaTypeTree(rhs)(tparams1, body1), tparams1, body1)
1423       case rhs =>
1424         typedType(rhs)
1425     }
1426     assignType(cpy.TypeDef(tdef)(name, rhs1), sym)
1427   }
1428 
1429   def typedClassDef(cdef: untpd.TypeDef, cls: ClassSymbol)(implicit ctx: Context) = track("typedClassDef") {
1430     val TypeDef(name, impl @ Template(constr, parents, self, _)) = cdef
1431     val superCtx = ctx.superCallContext
1432 
1433     /** If `ref` is an implicitly parameterized trait, pass an implicit argument list.
1434      *  Otherwise, if `ref` is a parameterized trait, error.
1435      *  Note: Traits and classes currently always have at least an empty parameter list ()
1436      *        before the implicit parameters (this is inserted if not given in source).
1437      *        We skip this parameter list when deciding whether a trait is parameterless or not.
1438      *  @param ref   The tree referring to the (parent) trait
1439      *  @param psym  Its type symbol
1440      *  @param cinfo The info of its constructor
1441      */
1442     def maybeCall(ref: Tree, psym: Symbol, cinfo: Type): Tree = cinfo.stripPoly match {
1443       case cinfo @ MethodType(Nil) if cinfo.resultType.isImplicitMethod =>
1444         val icall = New(ref).select(nme.CONSTRUCTOR).appliedToNone
1445         typedExpr(untpd.TypedSplice(icall))(superCtx)
1446       case cinfo @ MethodType(Nil) if !cinfo.resultType.isInstanceOf[MethodType] =>
1447         ref
1448       case cinfo: MethodType =>
1449         if (!ctx.erasedTypes) { // after constructors arguments are passed in super call.
1450           typr.println(i"constr type: $cinfo")
1451           ctx.error(ParameterizedTypeLacksArguments(psym), ref.pos)
1452         }
1453         ref
1454       case _ =>
1455         ref
1456     }
1457 
1458     def typedParent(tree: untpd.Tree): Tree = {
1459       var result = if (tree.isType) typedType(tree)(superCtx) else typedExpr(tree)(superCtx)
1460       val psym = result.tpe.typeSymbol
1461       if (tree.isType) {
1462         if (psym.is(Trait) && !cls.is(Trait) && !cls.superClass.isSubClass(psym))
1463           result = maybeCall(result, psym, psym.primaryConstructor.info)
1464       }
1465       else checkParentCall(result, cls)
1466       checkTraitInheritance(psym, cls, tree.pos)
1467       if (cls is Case) checkCaseInheritance(psym, cls, tree.pos)
1468       result
1469     }
1470 
1471     /** Checks if one of the decls is a type with the same name as class type member in selfType */
1472     def classExistsOnSelf(decls: Scope, self: tpd.ValDef): Boolean = {
1473       val selfType = self.tpt.tpe
1474       if (!selfType.exists || (selfType.classSymbol eq cls)) false
1475       else {
1476         def memberInSelfButNotThis(decl: Symbol) =
1477           selfType.member(decl.name).symbol.filter(other => other.isClass && other.owner != cls)
1478         decls.iterator.filter(_.isType).foldLeft(false) { (foundRedef, decl) =>
1479           val other = memberInSelfButNotThis(decl)
1480           if (other.exists) {
1481             val msg = CannotHaveSameNameAs(decl, other, CannotHaveSameNameAs.DefinedInSelf(self))
1482             ctx.error(msg, decl.pos)
1483           }
1484           foundRedef || other.exists
1485         }
1486       }
1487     }
1488 
1489     completeAnnotations(cdef, cls)
1490     val constr1 = typed(constr).asInstanceOf[DefDef]
1491     val parentsWithClass = ensureFirstTreeIsClass(parents mapconserve typedParent, cdef.namePos)
1492     val parents1 = ensureConstrCall(cls, parentsWithClass)(superCtx)
1493     val self1 = typed(self)(ctx.outer).asInstanceOf[ValDef] // outer context where class members are not visible
1494     if (self1.tpt.tpe.isError || classExistsOnSelf(cls.unforcedDecls, self1)) {
1495       // fail fast to avoid typing the body with an error type
1496       cdef.withType(UnspecifiedErrorType)
1497     } else {
1498       val dummy = localDummy(cls, impl)
1499       val body1 = typedStats(impl.body, dummy)(inClassContext(self1.symbol))
1500       if (!ctx.isAfterTyper)
1501         cls.setNoInitsFlags((NoInitsInterface /: body1) ((fs, stat) => fs & defKind(stat)))
1502 
1503       // Expand comments and type usecases
1504       cookComments(body1.map(_.symbol), self1.symbol)(localContext(cdef, cls).setNewScope)
1505 
1506       checkNoDoubleDefs(cls)
1507       val impl1 = cpy.Template(impl)(constr1, parents1, self1, body1)
1508         .withType(dummy.termRef)
1509       checkVariance(impl1)
1510       if (!cls.is(AbstractOrTrait) && !ctx.isAfterTyper)
1511         checkRealizableBounds(cls, cdef.namePos)
1512       val cdef1 = assignType(cpy.TypeDef(cdef)(name, impl1), cls)
1513       if (ctx.phase.isTyper && cdef1.tpe.derivesFrom(defn.DynamicClass) && !ctx.dynamicsEnabled) {
1514         val isRequired = parents1.exists(_.tpe.isRef(defn.DynamicClass))
1515         ctx.featureWarning(nme.dynamics.toString, "extension of type scala.Dynamic", isScala2Feature = true,
1516           cls, isRequired, cdef.pos)
1517       }
1518 
1519       // Check that phantom lattices are defined in a static object
1520       if (cls.classParents.exists(_.typeSymbol eq defn.PhantomClass) && !cls.isStaticOwner)
1521         ctx.error("only static objects can extend scala.Phantom", cdef.pos)
1522 
1523       // check value class constraints
1524       checkDerivedValueClass(cls, body1)
1525 
1526       cls.registerTree(cdef1)
1527 
1528       cdef1
1529 
1530       // todo later: check that
1531       //  1. If class is non-abstract, it is instantiatable:
1532       //  - self type is s supertype of own type
1533       //  - all type members have consistent bounds
1534       // 2. all private type members have consistent bounds
1535       // 3. Types do not override classes.
1536       // 4. Polymorphic type defs override nothing.
1537     }
1538   }
1539 
1540   /** Ensure that the first type in a list of parent types Ps points to a non-trait class.
1541    *  If that's not already the case, add one. The added class type CT is determined as follows.
1542    *  First, let C be the unique class such that
1543    *  - there is a parent P_i such that P_i derives from C, and
1544    *  - for every class D: If some parent P_j, j <= i derives from D, then C derives from D.
1545    *  Then, let CT be the smallest type which
1546    *  - has C as its class symbol, and
1547    *  - for all parents P_i: If P_i derives from C then P_i <:< CT.
1548    */
1549   def ensureFirstIsClass(parents: List[Type], pos: Position)(implicit ctx: Context): List[Type] = {
1550     def realClassParent(cls: Symbol): ClassSymbol =
1551       if (!cls.isClass) defn.ObjectClass
1552       else if (!(cls is Trait)) cls.asClass
1553       else cls.asClass.classParents match {
1554         case parentRef :: _ => realClassParent(parentRef.typeSymbol)
1555         case nil => defn.ObjectClass
1556       }
1557     def improve(candidate: ClassSymbol, parent: Type): ClassSymbol = {
1558       val pcls = realClassParent(parent.classSymbol)
1559       if (pcls derivesFrom candidate) pcls else candidate
1560     }
1561     parents match {
1562       case p :: _ if p.classSymbol.isRealClass => parents
1563       case _ =>
1564         val pcls = (defn.ObjectClass /: parents)(improve)
1565         typr.println(i"ensure first is class $parents%, % --> ${parents map (_ baseType pcls)}%, %")
1566         val first = ctx.typeComparer.glb(defn.ObjectType :: parents.map(_.baseType(pcls)))
1567         checkFeasibleParent(first, pos, em" in inferred superclass $first") :: parents
1568     }
1569   }
1570 
1571   /** Ensure that first parent tree refers to a real class. */
1572   def ensureFirstTreeIsClass(parents: List[Tree], pos: Position)(implicit ctx: Context): List[Tree] = parents match {
1573     case p :: ps if p.tpe.classSymbol.isRealClass => parents
1574     case _ => TypeTree(ensureFirstIsClass(parents.tpes, pos).head).withPos(pos) :: parents
1575   }
1576 
1577   /** If this is a real class, make sure its first parent is a
1578    *  constructor call. Cannot simply use a type. Overridden in ReTyper.
1579    */
1580   def ensureConstrCall(cls: ClassSymbol, parents: List[Tree])(implicit ctx: Context): List[Tree] = {
1581     val firstParent :: otherParents = parents
1582     if (firstParent.isType && !(cls is Trait) && !cls.is(JavaDefined))
1583       typed(untpd.New(untpd.TypedSplice(firstParent), Nil)) :: otherParents
1584     else parents
1585   }

1587   /** Overridden in retyper */
1588   def checkVariance(tree: Tree)(implicit ctx: Context) = VarianceChecker.check(tree)

1590   def localDummy(cls: ClassSymbol, impl: untpd.Template)(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol =
1591     ctx.newLocalDummy(cls, impl.pos)

1593   def typedImport(imp: untpd.Import, sym: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Import = track("typedImport") {
1594     val expr1 = typedExpr(imp.expr, AnySelectionProto)
1595     checkStable(expr1.tpe, imp.expr.pos)
1596     if (!ctx.isAfterTyper) checkRealizable(expr1.tpe, imp.expr.pos)
1597     assignType(cpy.Import(imp)(expr1, imp.selectors), sym)
1598   }

1600   def typedPackageDef(tree: untpd.PackageDef)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedPackageDef") {
1601     val pid1 = typedExpr(tree.pid, AnySelectionProto)(ctx.addMode(Mode.InPackageClauseName))
1602     val pkg = pid1.symbol
1603 
1604     // Package will not exist if a duplicate type has already been entered, see
1605     // `tests/neg/1708.scala`, else branch's error message should be supressed
1606     if (pkg.exists) {
1607       val packageContext =
1608         if (pkg is Package) ctx.fresh.setOwner(pkg.moduleClass).setTree(tree)
1609         else {
1610           ctx.error(PackageNameAlreadyDefined(pkg), tree.pos)
1611           ctx
1612         }
1613       val stats1 = typedStats(tree.stats, pkg.moduleClass)(packageContext)
1614       cpy.PackageDef(tree)(pid1.asInstanceOf[RefTree], stats1) withType pkg.termRef
1615     } else errorTree(tree, i"package ${tree.pid.name} does not exist")
1616   }

1618   def typedAnnotated(tree: untpd.Annotated, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = track("typedAnnotated") {
1619     val annot1 = typedExpr(tree.annot, defn.AnnotationType)
1620     val arg1 = typed(tree.arg, pt)
1621     if (ctx.mode is Mode.Type)
1622       assignType(cpy.Annotated(tree)(arg1, annot1), arg1, annot1)
1623     else {
1624       val tpt = TypeTree(AnnotatedType(arg1.tpe, Annotation(annot1)))
1625       assignType(cpy.Typed(tree)(arg1, tpt), tpt)
1626     }
1627   }

1629   def typedTypedSplice(tree: untpd.TypedSplice)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree =
1630     tree.tree match {
1631       case tree1: TypeTree => tree1  // no change owner necessary here ...
1632       case tree1: Ident => tree1     // ... or here, since these trees cannot contain bindings
1633       case tree1 =>
1634         if (ctx.owner ne tree.owner) tree1.changeOwner(tree.owner, ctx.owner)
1635         else tree1
1636     }
