1639   def typedAsFunction(tree: untpd.PostfixOp, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = {
1640     val untpd.PostfixOp(qual, Ident(nme.WILDCARD)) = tree
1641     val pt1 = if (defn.isFunctionType(pt)) pt else AnyFunctionProto
1642     val nestedCtx = ctx.fresh.setNewTyperState()
1643     val res = typed(qual, pt1)(nestedCtx)
1644     res match {
1645       case res @ closure(_, _, _) =>
1646       case _ =>
1647         ctx.errorOrMigrationWarning(OnlyFunctionsCanBeFollowedByUnderscore(res.tpe), tree.pos)
1648         if (ctx.scala2Mode) {
1649           // Under -rewrite, patch `x _` to `(() => x)`
1650           patch(Position(tree.pos.start), "(() => ")
1651           patch(Position(qual.pos.end, tree.pos.end), ")")
1652           return typed(untpd.Function(Nil, qual), pt)
1653         }
1654     }
1655     nestedCtx.typerState.commit()
1656     if (ctx.settings.strict.value) {
1657       lazy val (prefix, suffix) = res match {
1658         case Block(mdef @ DefDef(_, _, vparams :: Nil, _, _) :: Nil, _: Closure) =>
1659           val arity = vparams.length
1660           if (arity > 0) ("", "") else ("(() => ", "())")
1661         case _ =>
1662           ("(() => ", ")")
1663       }
1664       def remedy =
1665         if ((prefix ++ suffix).isEmpty) "simply leave out the trailing ` _`"
1666         else s"use `$prefix<function>$suffix` instead"
1667       ctx.errorOrMigrationWarning(i"""The syntax `<function> _` is no longer supported;
1668                                      |you can $remedy""", tree.pos)
1669       if (ctx.scala2Mode) {
1670         patch(Position(tree.pos.start), prefix)
1671         patch(Position(qual.pos.end, tree.pos.end), suffix)
1672       }
1673     }
1674     res
1675   }
1676 
1677   /** Translate infix operation expression `l op r` to
1678    *
1679    *    l.op(r)   			    if `op` is left-associative
1680    *    { val x = l; r.op(l) }  if `op` is right-associative call-by-value and `l` is impure
1681    *    r.op(l)                 if `op` is right-associative call-by-name or `l` is pure
1682    */
1683   def typedInfixOp(tree: untpd.InfixOp, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = {
1684     val untpd.InfixOp(l, op, r) = tree
1685     val app = typedApply(desugar.binop(l, op, r), pt)
1686     if (untpd.isLeftAssoc(op.name)) app
1687     else {
1688       val defs = new mutable.ListBuffer[Tree]
1689       def lift(app: Tree): Tree = (app: @unchecked) match {
1690         case Apply(fn, args) =>
1691           if (app.tpe.isError) app
1692           else tpd.cpy.Apply(app)(fn, LiftImpure.liftArgs(defs, fn.tpe, args))
1693         case Assign(lhs, rhs) =>
1694           tpd.cpy.Assign(app)(lhs, lift(rhs))
1695         case Block(stats, expr) =>
1696           tpd.cpy.Block(app)(stats, lift(expr))
1697       }
1698       Applications.wrapDefs(defs, lift(app))
1699     }
1700   }

1702   /** Retrieve symbol attached to given tree */
1703   protected def retrieveSym(tree: untpd.Tree)(implicit ctx: Context) = tree.removeAttachment(SymOfTree) match {
1704     case Some(sym) =>
1705       sym.ensureCompleted()
1706       sym
1707     case none =>
1708       NoSymbol
1709   }
1710 
1711   /** A fresh local context with given tree and owner.
1712    *  Owner might not exist (can happen for self valdefs), in which case
1713    *  no owner is set in result context
1714    */
1715   protected def localContext(tree: untpd.Tree, owner: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): FreshContext = {
1716     val freshCtx = ctx.fresh.setTree(tree)
1717     if (owner.exists) freshCtx.setOwner(owner) else freshCtx
1718   }
1719 
1720   protected def localTyper(sym: Symbol): Typer = nestedTyper.remove(sym).get
1721 
1722   def typedUnadapted(initTree: untpd.Tree, pt: Type = WildcardType)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = {
1723     record("typedUnadapted")
1724     val xtree = expanded(initTree)
1725     xtree.removeAttachment(TypedAhead) match {
1726       case Some(ttree) => ttree
1727       case none =>
1728 
1729         def typedNamed(tree: untpd.NameTree, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = {
1730           val sym = retrieveSym(xtree)
1731           tree match {
1732             case tree: untpd.Ident => typedIdent(tree, pt)
1733             case tree: untpd.Select => typedSelect(tree, pt)
1734             case tree: untpd.Bind => typedBind(tree, pt)
1735             case tree: untpd.ValDef =>
1736               if (tree.isEmpty) tpd.EmptyValDef
1737               else typedValDef(tree, sym)(localContext(tree, sym).setNewScope)
1738             case tree: untpd.DefDef =>
1739               val typer1 = localTyper(sym)
1740               typer1.typedDefDef(tree, sym)(localContext(tree, sym).setTyper(typer1))
1741             case tree: untpd.TypeDef =>
1742               if (tree.isClassDef)
1743                 typedClassDef(tree, sym.asClass)(localContext(tree, sym).setMode(ctx.mode &~ Mode.InSuperCall))
1744               else
1745                 typedTypeDef(tree, sym)(localContext(tree, sym).setNewScope)
1746             case _ => typedUnadapted(desugar(tree), pt)
1747           }
1748         }
1749 
1750         def typedUnnamed(tree: untpd.Tree): Tree = tree match {
1751           case tree: untpd.Apply =>
1752             if (ctx.mode is Mode.Pattern) typedUnApply(tree, pt) else typedApply(tree, pt)
1753           case tree: untpd.This => typedThis(tree)
1754           case tree: untpd.Literal => typedLiteral(tree)
1755           case tree: untpd.New => typedNew(tree, pt)
1756           case tree: untpd.Typed => typedTyped(tree, pt)
1757           case tree: untpd.NamedArg => typedNamedArg(tree, pt)
1758           case tree: untpd.Assign => typedAssign(tree, pt)
1759           case tree: untpd.Block => typedBlock(desugar.block(tree), pt)(ctx.fresh.setNewScope)
1760           case tree: untpd.If => typedIf(tree, pt)
1761           case tree: untpd.Function => typedFunction(tree, pt)
1762           case tree: untpd.Closure => typedClosure(tree, pt)
1763           case tree: untpd.Import => typedImport(tree, retrieveSym(tree))
1764           case tree: untpd.Match => typedMatch(tree, pt)
1765           case tree: untpd.Return => typedReturn(tree)
1766           case tree: untpd.Try => typedTry(tree, pt)
1767           case tree: untpd.Throw => typedThrow(tree)
1768           case tree: untpd.TypeApply => typedTypeApply(tree, pt)
1769           case tree: untpd.Super => typedSuper(tree, pt)
1770           case tree: untpd.SeqLiteral => typedSeqLiteral(tree, pt)
1771           case tree: untpd.Inlined => typedInlined(tree, pt)
1772           case tree: untpd.Quote => typedQuote(tree, pt)
1773           case tree: untpd.TypeTree => typedTypeTree(tree, pt)
1774           case tree: untpd.SingletonTypeTree => typedSingletonTypeTree(tree)
1775           case tree: untpd.AndTypeTree => typedAndTypeTree(tree)
1776           case tree: untpd.OrTypeTree => typedOrTypeTree(tree)
1777           case tree: untpd.RefinedTypeTree => typedRefinedTypeTree(tree)
1778           case tree: untpd.AppliedTypeTree => typedAppliedTypeTree(tree)
1779           case tree: untpd.LambdaTypeTree => typedLambdaTypeTree(tree)(localContext(tree, NoSymbol).setNewScope)
1780           case tree: untpd.ByNameTypeTree => typedByNameTypeTree(tree)
1781           case tree: untpd.TypeBoundsTree => typedTypeBoundsTree(tree, pt)
1782           case tree: untpd.Alternative => typedAlternative(tree, pt)
1783           case tree: untpd.PackageDef => typedPackageDef(tree)
1784           case tree: untpd.Annotated => typedAnnotated(tree, pt)
1785           case tree: untpd.TypedSplice => typedTypedSplice(tree)
1786           case tree: untpd.UnApply => typedUnApply(tree, pt)
1787           case tree: untpd.DependentTypeTree => typed(untpd.TypeTree().withPos(tree.pos), pt)
1788           case tree: untpd.InfixOp if ctx.mode.isExpr => typedInfixOp(tree, pt)
1789           case tree @ untpd.PostfixOp(qual, Ident(nme.WILDCARD)) => typedAsFunction(tree, pt)
1790           case untpd.EmptyTree => tpd.EmptyTree
1791           case _ => typedUnadapted(desugar(tree), pt)
1792         }
1793 
1794         val ifpt = defn.asImplicitFunctionType(pt)
1795         if (ifpt.exists &&
1796             xtree.isTerm &&
1797             !untpd.isImplicitClosure(xtree) &&
1798             !ctx.mode.is(Mode.ImplicitShadowing) &&
1799             !ctx.isAfterTyper)
1800           makeImplicitFunction(xtree, ifpt)
1801         else xtree match {
1802           case xtree: untpd.NameTree => typedNamed(xtree, pt)
1803           case xtree => typedUnnamed(xtree)
1804         }
1805     }
1806   }
1807 
1808   protected def makeImplicitFunction(tree: untpd.Tree, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = {
1809     val defn.FunctionOf(formals, _, true) = pt.dropDependentRefinement
1810     val ifun = desugar.makeImplicitFunction(formals, tree)
1811     typr.println(i"make implicit function $tree / $pt ---> $ifun")
1812     typed(ifun, pt)
1813   }
1814 
1815   def typed(tree: untpd.Tree, pt: Type = WildcardType)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = /*>|>*/ trace(i"typing $tree", typr, show = true) /*<|<*/ {
1816     record(s"typed $getClass")
1817     record("typed total")
1818     assertPositioned(tree)
1819     try adapt(typedUnadapted(tree, pt), pt)
1820     catch {
1821       case ex: CyclicReference => errorTree(tree, cyclicErrorMsg(ex))
1822       case ex: TypeError => errorTree(tree, ex.getMessage)
1823     }
1824   }
1825 
1826   def typedTrees(trees: List[untpd.Tree])(implicit ctx: Context): List[Tree] =
1827     trees mapconserve (typed(_))
1828 
1829   def typedStats(stats: List[untpd.Tree], exprOwner: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): List[tpd.Tree] = {
1830     val buf = new mutable.ListBuffer[Tree]
1831     @tailrec def traverse(stats: List[untpd.Tree])(implicit ctx: Context): List[Tree] = stats match {
1832       case (imp: untpd.Import) :: rest =>
1833         val imp1 = typed(imp)
1834         buf += imp1
1835         traverse(rest)(ctx.importContext(imp, imp1.symbol))
1836       case (mdef: untpd.DefTree) :: rest =>
1837         mdef.removeAttachment(ExpandedTree) match {
1838           case Some(xtree) =>
1839             traverse(xtree :: rest)
1840           case none =>
1841             typed(mdef) match {
1842               case mdef1: DefDef if Inliner.hasBodyToInline(mdef1.symbol) =>
1843                 buf ++= inlineExpansion(mdef1)
1844               case mdef1 =>
1845                 buf += mdef1
1846             }
1847             traverse(rest)
1848         }
1849       case Thicket(stats) :: rest =>
1850         traverse(stats ++ rest)
1851       case stat :: rest =>
1852         val stat1 = typed(stat)(ctx.exprContext(stat, exprOwner))
1853         if (!ctx.isAfterTyper && isPureExpr(stat1) && !stat1.tpe.isRef(defn.UnitClass))
1854           ctx.warning(em"a pure expression does nothing in statement position", stat.pos)
1855         buf += stat1
1856         traverse(rest)
1857       case nil =>
1858         buf.toList
1859     }
1860     val localCtx = {
1861       val exprOwnerOpt = if (exprOwner == ctx.owner) None else Some(exprOwner)
1862       ctx.withProperty(ExprOwner, exprOwnerOpt)
1863     }
1864     traverse(stats)(localCtx)
1865   }
1866 
1867   /** Given an inline method `mdef`, the method rewritten so that its body
1868    *  uses accessors to access non-public members, followed by the accessor definitions.
1869    *  Overwritten in Retyper to return `mdef` unchanged.
1870    */
1871   protected def inlineExpansion(mdef: DefDef)(implicit ctx: Context): List[Tree] =
1872     tpd.cpy.DefDef(mdef)(rhs = Inliner.bodyToInline(mdef.symbol)) ::
1873         Inliner.removeInlineAccessors(mdef.symbol)
1874 
1875   def typedExpr(tree: untpd.Tree, pt: Type = WildcardType)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree =
1876     typed(tree, pt)(ctx retractMode Mode.PatternOrTypeBits)
1877   def typedType(tree: untpd.Tree, pt: Type = WildcardType)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = // todo: retract mode between Type and Pattern?
1878     typed(tree, pt)(ctx addMode Mode.Type)
1879   def typedPattern(tree: untpd.Tree, selType: Type = WildcardType)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree =
1880     typed(tree, selType)(ctx addMode Mode.Pattern)
1881 
1882   def tryEither[T](op: Context => T)(fallBack: (T, TyperState) => T)(implicit ctx: Context) = {
1883     val nestedCtx = ctx.fresh.setNewTyperState()
1884     val result = op(nestedCtx)
1885     if (nestedCtx.reporter.hasErrors)
1886       fallBack(result, nestedCtx.typerState)
1887     else {
1888       nestedCtx.typerState.commit()
1889       result
1890     }
1891   }
1892 
1893   /** Try `op1`, if there are errors, try `op2`, if `op2` also causes errors, fall back
1894    *  to errors and result of `op1`.
1895    */
1896   def tryAlternatively[T](op1: Context => T)(op2: Context => T)(implicit ctx: Context): T =
1897     tryEither(op1) { (failedVal, failedState) =>
1898       tryEither(op2) { (_, _) =>
1899         failedState.commit()
1900         failedVal
1901       }
1902     }
1903 
1904   /** Is `pt` a prototype of an `apply` selection, or a parameterless function yielding one? */
1905   def isApplyProto(pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = pt match {
1906     case pt: SelectionProto => pt.name == nme.apply
1907     case pt: FunProto       => pt.args.isEmpty && isApplyProto(pt.resultType)
1908     case pt: IgnoredProto   => isApplyProto(pt.ignored)
1909     case _                  => false
1910   }
1911 
1912   /** Potentially add apply node or implicit conversions. Before trying either,
1913    *  if the function is applied to an empty parameter list (), we try
1914    *
1915    *  0th strategy: If `tree` overrides a nullary method, mark the prototype
1916    *                so that the argument is dropped and return `tree` itself.
1917    *                (but do this at most once per tree).
1918    *
1919    *  After that, two strategies are tried, and the first that is successful is picked.
1920    *  If neither of the strategies are successful, continues with`fallBack`.
1921    *
1922    *  1st strategy: Try to insert `.apply` so that the result conforms to prototype `pt`.
1923    *                This strategy is not tried if the prototype represents already
1924    *                another `.apply` or `.apply()` selection.
1925    *
1926    *  2nd strategy: If tree is a select `qual.name`, try to insert an implicit conversion
1927    *    around the qualifier part `qual` so that the result conforms to the expected type
1928    *    with wildcard result type.
1929    */
1930   def tryInsertApplyOrImplicit(tree: Tree, pt: ProtoType)(fallBack: => Tree)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = {
1931 
1932     def isMethod(tree: Tree) = tree.tpe match {
1933       case ref: TermRef => ref.denot.alternatives.forall(_.info.widen.isInstanceOf[MethodicType])
1934       case _ => false
1935     }
1936 
1937     def isSyntheticApply(tree: Tree): Boolean = tree match {
1938       case tree: Select => tree.getAttachment(InsertedApply).isDefined
1939       case Apply(fn, _) => fn.getAttachment(InsertedApply).isDefined
1940       case _ => false
1941     }
1942 
1943     def tryApply(implicit ctx: Context) = {
1944       val sel = typedSelect(untpd.Select(untpd.TypedSplice(tree), nme.apply), pt)
1945       sel.pushAttachment(InsertedApply, ())
1946       if (sel.tpe.isError) sel
1947       else try adapt(sel, pt) finally sel.removeAttachment(InsertedApply)
1948     }
1949 
1950     def tryImplicit =
1951       tryInsertImplicitOnQualifier(tree, pt).getOrElse(fallBack)
1952 
1953     pt match {
1954       case pt @ FunProto(Nil, _, _)
1955       if tree.symbol.allOverriddenSymbols.exists(_.info.isNullaryMethod) &&
1956          tree.getAttachment(DroppedEmptyArgs).isEmpty =>
1957         tree.putAttachment(DroppedEmptyArgs, ())
1958         pt.markAsDropped()
1959         tree
1960       case _ =>
1961         if (isApplyProto(pt) || isMethod(tree) || isSyntheticApply(tree)) tryImplicit
1962         else tryEither(tryApply(_))((_, _) => tryImplicit)
1963      }
1964   }
1965 
1966   /** If this tree is a select node `qual.name`, try to insert an implicit conversion
1967    *  `c` around `qual` so that `c(qual).name` conforms to `pt`.
1968    */
1969   def tryInsertImplicitOnQualifier(tree: Tree, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Option[Tree] = trace(i"try insert impl on qualifier $tree $pt") {
1970     tree match {
1971       case Select(qual, name) if name != nme.CONSTRUCTOR =>
1972         val qualProto = SelectionProto(name, pt, NoViewsAllowed, privateOK = false)
1973         tryEither { implicit ctx =>
1974           val qual1 = adaptInterpolated(qual, qualProto)
1975           if ((qual eq qual1) || ctx.reporter.hasErrors) None
1976           else Some(typed(cpy.Select(tree)(untpd.TypedSplice(qual1), name), pt))
1977         } { (_, _) => None
1978         }
1979       case _ => None
1980     }
1981   }
1982 
1983   def adapt(tree: Tree, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = /*>|>*/ track("adapt") /*<|<*/ {
1984     /*>|>*/ trace(i"adapting $tree of type ${tree.tpe} to $pt", typr, show = true) /*<|<*/ {
1985       if (!tree.denot.isOverloaded) {
1986       	// for overloaded trees: resolve overloading before simplifying
1987         if (tree.isDef) interpolateUndetVars(tree, tree.symbol, pt)
1988         else if (!tree.tpe.widen.isInstanceOf[LambdaType]) interpolateUndetVars(tree, NoSymbol, pt)
1989         tree.overwriteType(tree.tpe.simplified)
1990       }
1991       adaptInterpolated(tree, pt)
1992     }
1993   }
1994 
1995   /** (-1) For expressions with annotated types, let AnnotationCheckers decide what to do
1996    *  (0) Convert expressions with constant types to literals (unless in interactive/scaladoc mode)
1997    */
1998 
1999   /** Perform the following adaptations of expression, pattern or type `tree` wrt to
2000    *  given prototype `pt`:
2001    *  (1) Resolve overloading
2002    *  (2) Apply parameterless functions
2003    *  (3) Apply polymorphic types to fresh instances of their type parameters and
2004    *      store these instances in context.undetparams,
2005    *      unless followed by explicit type application.
2006    *  (4) Do the following to unapplied methods used as values:
2007    *  (4.1) If the method has only implicit parameters pass implicit arguments
2008    *  (4.2) otherwise, if `pt` is a function type and method is not a constructor,
2009    *        convert to function by eta-expansion,
2010    *  (4.3) otherwise, if the method is nullary with a result type compatible to `pt`
2011    *        and it is not a constructor, apply it to ()
2012    *  otherwise issue an error
2013    *  (5) Convert constructors in a pattern as follows:
2014    *  (5.1) If constructor refers to a case class factory, set tree's type to the unique
2015    *        instance of its primary constructor that is a subtype of the expected type.
2016    *  (5.2) If constructor refers to an extractor, convert to application of
2017    *        unapply or unapplySeq method.
2018    *
2019    *  (6) Convert all other types to TypeTree nodes.
2020    *  (7) When in TYPEmode but not FUNmode or HKmode, check that types are fully parameterized
2021    *      (7.1) In HKmode, higher-kinded types are allowed, but they must have the expected kind-arity
2022    *  (8) When in both EXPRmode and FUNmode, add apply method calls to values of object type.
2023    *  (9) If there are undetermined type variables and not POLYmode, infer expression instance
2024    *  Then, if tree's type is not a subtype of expected type, try the following adaptations:
2025    *  (10) If the expected type is Byte, Short or Char, and the expression
2026    *      is an integer fitting in the range of that type, convert it to that type.
2027    *  (11) Widen numeric literals to their expected type, if necessary
2028    *  (12) When in mode EXPRmode, convert E to { E; () } if expected type is scala.Unit.
2029    *  (13) When in mode EXPRmode, apply AnnotationChecker conversion if expected type is annotated.
2030    *  (14) When in mode EXPRmode, apply a view
2031    *  If all this fails, error
2032    */
2033   def adaptInterpolated(tree: Tree, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Tree = {
2034 
2035     assert(pt.exists)
2036 
2037     def methodStr = err.refStr(methPart(tree).tpe)
2038 
2039     def missingArgs(mt: MethodType) = {
2040       ctx.error(MissingEmptyArgumentList(methPart(tree).symbol), tree.pos)
2041       tree.withType(mt.resultType)
2042     }
2043 
2044     def adaptOverloaded(ref: TermRef) = {
2045       val altDenots = ref.denot.alternatives
2046       typr.println(i"adapt overloaded $ref with alternatives ${altDenots map (_.info)}%, %")
2047       val alts = altDenots.map(TermRef(ref.prefix, ref.name, _))
2048       resolveOverloaded(alts, pt) match {
2049         case alt :: Nil =>
2050           adapt(tree.withType(alt), pt)
2051         case Nil =>
2052           def noMatches =
2053             errorTree(tree,
2054               em"""none of the ${err.overloadedAltsStr(altDenots)}
2055                   |match ${err.expectedTypeStr(pt)}""")
2056           def hasEmptyParams(denot: SingleDenotation) = denot.info.paramInfoss == ListOfNil
2057           pt match {
2058             case pt: FunProto =>
2059               tryInsertApplyOrImplicit(tree, pt)(noMatches)
2060             case _ =>
2061               if (altDenots exists (_.info.paramInfoss == ListOfNil))
2062                 typed(untpd.Apply(untpd.TypedSplice(tree), Nil), pt)
2063               else
2064                 noMatches
2065           }
2066         case alts =>
2067           val remainingDenots = alts map (_.denot.asInstanceOf[SingleDenotation])
2068           errorTree(tree, AmbiguousOverload(tree, remainingDenots, pt)(err))
2069       }
2070     }

2072     def isUnary(tp: Type): Boolean = tp match {
2073       case tp: MethodicType =>
2074         tp.firstParamTypes match {
2075           case ptype :: Nil => !ptype.isRepeatedParam
2076           case _ => false
2077         }
2078       case tp: TermRef =>
2079         tp.denot.alternatives.forall(alt => isUnary(alt.info))
2080       case _ =>
2081         false
2082     }
2083 
2084     def adaptToArgs(wtp: Type, pt: FunProto): Tree = wtp match {
2085       case _: MethodOrPoly =>
2086         if (pt.args.lengthCompare(1) > 0 && isUnary(wtp) && ctx.canAutoTuple)
2087           adaptInterpolated(tree, pt.tupled)
2088         else
2089           tree
2090       case _ => tryInsertApplyOrImplicit(tree, pt) {
2091         errorTree(tree, MethodDoesNotTakeParameters(tree, methPart(tree).tpe)(err))
2092       }
2093     }
2094 
2095     /** If `tp` is a TypeVar which is fully constrained (i.e. its upper bound `hi` conforms
2096      *  to its lower bound `lo`), replace `tp` by `hi`. This is necessary to
2097      *  keep the right constraints for some implicit search problems. The paradigmatic case
2098      *  is `implicitNums.scala`. Without the healing done in `followAlias`, we cannot infer
2099      *  implicitly[_3], where _2 is the typelevel number 3. The problem here is that if a
2100      *  prototype is, say, Succ[Succ[Zero]], we can infer that it's argument type is Succ[Zero].
2101      *  But if the prototype is N? >: Succ[Succ[Zero]] <: Succ[Succ[Zero]], the same
2102      *  decomposition does not work - we'd get a N?#M where M is the element type name of Succ
2103      *  instead.
2104      */
2105     def followAlias(tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
2106       val constraint = ctx.typerState.constraint
2107       def inst(tp: Type): Type = tp match {
2108         case TypeBounds(lo, hi)
2109         if (lo eq hi) || ctx.test(implicit ctx => hi <:< lo) =>
2110           inst(lo)
2111         case tp: TypeParamRef =>
2112           constraint.typeVarOfParam(tp).orElse(tp)
2113         case _ => tp
2114       }
2115       tp match {
2116         case tp: TypeVar if constraint.contains(tp) => inst(constraint.entry(tp.origin))
2117         case _ => tp
2118       }
2119     }
2120 
2121     def adaptNoArgsImplicitMethod(wtp: MethodType): Tree = {
2122       assert(wtp.isImplicitMethod)
2123       val tvarsToInstantiate = tvarsInParams(tree)
2124       wtp.paramInfos.foreach(instantiateSelected(_, tvarsToInstantiate))
2125       val constr = ctx.typerState.constraint
2126 
2127       def dummyArg(tp: Type) = untpd.Ident(nme.???).withTypeUnchecked(tp)
2128 
2129       def addImplicitArgs(implicit ctx: Context) = {
2130         def implicitArgs(formals: List[Type]): List[Tree] = formals match {
2131           case Nil => Nil
2132           case formal :: formals1 =>
2133             val arg = inferImplicitArg(formal, tree.pos.endPos)
2134             arg.tpe match {
2135               case failed: SearchFailureType
2136               if !failed.isInstanceOf[AmbiguousImplicits] && !tree.symbol.hasDefaultParams =>
2137                 // no need to search further, the adapt fails in any case
2138                 // the reason why we continue inferring arguments in case of an AmbiguousImplicits
2139                 // is that we need to know whether there are further errors.
2140                 // If there are none, we have to propagate the ambiguity to the caller.
2141                 arg :: formals1.map(dummyArg)
2142               case _ =>
2143                 arg :: implicitArgs(formals1)
2144             }
2145         }
2146         val args = implicitArgs(wtp.paramInfos)
2147 
2148         def propagatedFailure(args: List[Tree]): Type = args match {
2149           case arg :: args1 =>
2150             arg.tpe match {
2151               case ambi: AmbiguousImplicits =>
2152                 propagatedFailure(args1) match {
2153                   case NoType | (_: AmbiguousImplicits) => ambi
2154                   case failed => failed
2155                 }
2156               case failed: SearchFailureType => failed
2157               case _ => propagatedFailure(args1)
2158             }
2159           case Nil => NoType
2160         }
2161 
2162         val propFail = propagatedFailure(args)
2163 
2164         def issueErrors(): Tree = {
2165           (wtp.paramNames, wtp.paramInfos, args).zipped.foreach { (paramName, formal, arg) =>
2166             arg.tpe match {
2167               case failure: SearchFailureType =>
2168                 ctx.error(
2169                   missingArgMsg(arg, formal, implicitParamString(paramName, methodStr, tree)),
2170                   tree.pos.endPos)
2171               case _ =>
2172             }
2173           }
2174           untpd.Apply(tree, args).withType(propFail)
2175         }
2176 
2177         if (propFail.exists) {
2178           // If there are several arguments, some arguments might already
2179           // have influenced the context, binding variables, but later ones
2180           // might fail. In that case the constraint needs to be reset.
2181           ctx.typerState.constraint = constr
2182 
2183           // If method has default params, fall back to regular application
2184           // where all inferred implicits are passed as named args.
2185           if (tree.symbol.hasDefaultParams && !propFail.isInstanceOf[AmbiguousImplicits]) {
2186             val namedArgs = (wtp.paramNames, args).zipped.flatMap { (pname, arg) =>
2187               if (arg.tpe.isError) Nil else untpd.NamedArg(pname, untpd.TypedSplice(arg)) :: Nil
2188             }
2189             tryEither { implicit ctx =>
2190               typed(untpd.Apply(untpd.TypedSplice(tree), namedArgs), pt)
2191             } { (_, _) =>
2192               issueErrors()
2193             }
2194           } else issueErrors()
2195         }
2196         else adapt(tpd.Apply(tree, args), pt)
2197       }
2198       addImplicitArgs(argCtx(tree))
2199     }
2200 
2201     /** A synthetic apply should be eta-expanded if it is the apply of an implicit function
2202       *  class, and the expected type is a function type. This rule is needed so we can pass
2203       *  an implicit function to a regular function type. So the following is OK
2204       *
2205       *     val f: implicit A => B  =  ???
2206       *     val g: A => B = f
2207       *
2208       *  and the last line expands to
2209       *
2210       *     val g: A => B  =  (x$0: A) => f.apply(x$0)
2211       *
2212       *  One could be tempted not to eta expand the rhs, but that would violate the invariant
2213       *  that expressions of implicit function types are always implicit closures, which is
2214       *  exploited by ShortcutImplicits.
2215       *
2216       *  On the other hand, the following would give an error if there is no implicit
2217       *  instance of A available.
2218       *
2219       *     val x: AnyRef = f
2220       *
2221       *  That's intentional, we want to fail here, otherwise some unsuccesful implicit searches
2222       *  would go undetected.
2223       *
2224       *  Examples for these cases are found in run/implicitFuns.scala and neg/i2006.scala.
2225       */
2226     def adaptNoArgsUnappliedMethod(wtp: MethodType, functionExpected: Boolean, arity: Int): Tree = {
2227       def isExpandableApply =
2228         defn.isImplicitFunctionClass(tree.symbol.maybeOwner) && functionExpected
2229 
2230       /** Is reference to this symbol `f` automatically expanded to `f()`? */
2231       def isAutoApplied(sym: Symbol): Boolean = {
2232         sym.isConstructor ||
2233         sym.matchNullaryLoosely ||
2234         ctx.testScala2Mode(MissingEmptyArgumentList(sym), tree.pos,
2235             patch(tree.pos.endPos, "()"))
2236       }
2237 
2238       // Reasons NOT to eta expand:
2239       //  - we reference a constructor
2240       //  - we are in a pattern
2241       //  - the current tree is a synthetic apply which is not expandable (eta-expasion would simply undo that)
2242       if (arity >= 0 &&
2243           !tree.symbol.isConstructor &&
2244           !ctx.mode.is(Mode.Pattern) &&
2245           !(isSyntheticApply(tree) && !isExpandableApply))
2246         typed(etaExpand(tree, wtp, arity), pt)
2247       else if (wtp.paramInfos.isEmpty && isAutoApplied(tree.symbol))
2248         adaptInterpolated(tpd.Apply(tree, Nil), pt)
2249       else if (wtp.isImplicitMethod)
2250         err.typeMismatch(tree, pt)
2251       else
2252         missingArgs(wtp)
2253     }
2254 
2255     def adaptNoArgsOther(wtp: Type) = {
2256       ctx.typeComparer.GADTused = false
2257       if (defn.isImplicitFunctionClass(wtp.underlyingClassRef(refinementOK = false).classSymbol) &&
2258           !untpd.isImplicitClosure(tree) &&
2259           !isApplyProto(pt) &&
2260           !ctx.isAfterTyper) {
2261         typr.println(i"insert apply on implicit $tree")
2262         typed(untpd.Select(untpd.TypedSplice(tree), nme.apply), pt)
2263       }
2264       else if (ctx.mode is Mode.Pattern) {
2265         checkEqualityEvidence(tree, pt)
2266         tree
2267       }
2268       else if (tree.tpe <:< pt) {
2269         if (pt.hasAnnotation(defn.InlineParamAnnot))
2270           checkInlineConformant(tree, "argument to inline parameter")
2271         if (Inliner.hasBodyToInline(tree.symbol) &&
2272             !ctx.owner.ownersIterator.exists(_.isInlineMethod) &&
2273             !ctx.settings.YnoInline.value &&
2274             !ctx.isAfterTyper &&
2275             !ctx.reporter.hasErrors)
2276           adapt(Inliner.inlineCall(tree, pt), pt)
2277         else if (ctx.typeComparer.GADTused && pt.isValueType)
2278           // Insert an explicit cast, so that -Ycheck in later phases succeeds.
2279           // I suspect, but am not 100% sure that this might affect inferred types,
2280           // if the expected type is a supertype of the GADT bound. It would be good to come
2281           // up with a test case for this.
2282           tree.asInstance(pt)
2283         else
2284           tree
2285       }
2286       else wtp match {
2287         case wtp: MethodType => missingArgs(wtp)
2288         case _ =>
2289           typr.println(i"adapt to subtype ${tree.tpe} !<:< $pt")
2290           //typr.println(TypeComparer.explained(implicit ctx => tree.tpe <:< pt))
2291           adaptToSubType(wtp)
2292       }
2293     }
2294 
2295     // Follow proxies and approximate type paramrefs by their upper bound
2296     // in the current constraint in order to figure out robustly
2297     // whether an expected type is some sort of function type.
2298     def underlyingApplied(tp: Type): Type = tp.stripTypeVar match {
2299       case tp: RefinedType => tp
2300       case tp: AppliedType => tp
2301       case tp: TypeParamRef => underlyingApplied(ctx.typeComparer.bounds(tp).hi)
2302       case tp: TypeProxy => underlyingApplied(tp.superType)
2303       case _ => tp
2304     }
2305 
2306     def adaptNoArgs(wtp: Type): Tree = {
2307       val ptNorm = underlyingApplied(pt)
2308       lazy val functionExpected = defn.isFunctionType(ptNorm)
2309       lazy val resultMatch = constrainResult(wtp, followAlias(pt))
2310       wtp match {
2311         case wtp: ExprType =>
2312           adaptInterpolated(tree.withType(wtp.resultType), pt)
2313         case wtp: MethodType if wtp.isImplicitMethod && (resultMatch || !functionExpected) =>
2314           if (resultMatch || ctx.mode.is(Mode.ImplicitsEnabled)) adaptNoArgsImplicitMethod(wtp)
2315           else {
2316             // Don't proceed with implicit search if result type cannot match - the search
2317             // will likely be under-constrained, which means that an unbounded number of alternatives
2318             // is tried. See strawman-contrib MapDecoratorTest.scala for an example where this happens.
2319             err.typeMismatch(tree, pt)
2320           }
2321         case wtp: MethodType if !pt.isSingleton =>
2322           val arity =
2323             if (functionExpected)
2324               if (!isFullyDefined(pt, ForceDegree.none) && isFullyDefined(wtp, ForceDegree.none))
2325                 // if method type is fully defined, but expected type is not,
2326                 // prioritize method parameter types as parameter types of the eta-expanded closure
2327                 0
2328               else defn.functionArity(ptNorm)
2329             else {
2330               val nparams = wtp.paramInfos.length
2331               if (nparams > 0 || pt.eq(AnyFunctionProto)) nparams
2332               else -1 // no eta expansion in this case
2333             }
2334             adaptNoArgsUnappliedMethod(wtp, functionExpected, arity)
2335         case _ =>
2336           adaptNoArgsOther(wtp)
2337       }
2338     }

2340     /** Adapt an expression of constant type to a different constant type `tpe`. */
2341     def adaptConstant(tree: Tree, tpe: ConstantType): Tree = {
2342       def lit = Literal(tpe.value).withPos(tree.pos)
2343       tree match {
2344         case Literal(c) => lit
2345         case tree @ Block(stats, expr) => tpd.cpy.Block(tree)(stats, adaptConstant(expr, tpe))
2346         case tree =>
2347           if (isIdempotentExpr(tree)) lit // See discussion in phase Literalize why we demand isIdempotentExpr
2348           else Block(tree :: Nil, lit)
2349       }
2350     }
2351 
2352     def toSAM(tree: Tree): Tree = tree match {
2353       case tree: Block => tpd.cpy.Block(tree)(tree.stats, toSAM(tree.expr))
2354       case tree: Closure => cpy.Closure(tree)(tpt = TypeTree(pt)).withType(pt)
2355     }
2356 
2357     def adaptToSubType(wtp: Type): Tree = {
2358       // try converting a constant to the target type
2359       val folded = ConstFold(tree, pt)
2360       if (folded ne tree) return adaptConstant(folded, folded.tpe.asInstanceOf[ConstantType])
2361       // drop type if prototype is Unit
2362       if (pt isRef defn.UnitClass)
2363         // local adaptation makes sure every adapted tree conforms to its pt
2364         // so will take the code path that decides on inlining
2365         return tpd.Block(adapt(tree, WildcardType) :: Nil, Literal(Constant(())))
2366       // convert function literal to SAM closure
2367       tree match {
2368         case closure(Nil, id @ Ident(nme.ANON_FUN), _)
2369         if defn.isFunctionType(wtp) && !defn.isFunctionType(pt) =>
2370           pt match {
2371             case SAMType(meth)
2372             if wtp <:< meth.info.toFunctionType() =>
2373               // was ... && isFullyDefined(pt, ForceDegree.noBottom)
2374               // but this prevents case blocks from implementing polymorphic partial functions,
2375               // since we do not know the result parameter a priori. Have to wait until the
2376               // body is typechecked.
2377               return toSAM(tree)
2378             case _ =>
2379           }
2380         case _ =>
2381       }
2382       // try an implicit conversion
2383       val prevConstraint = ctx.typerState.constraint
2384       def recover(failure: SearchFailureType) =
2385         if (isFullyDefined(wtp, force = ForceDegree.all) &&
2386             ctx.typerState.constraint.ne(prevConstraint)) adapt(tree, pt)
2387         else err.typeMismatch(tree, pt, failure)
2388       if (ctx.mode.is(Mode.ImplicitsEnabled))
2389         inferView(tree, pt) match {
2390           case SearchSuccess(inferred, _, _) =>
2391             adapt(inferred, pt)(ctx.retractMode(Mode.ImplicitsEnabled))
2392           case failure: SearchFailure =>
2393             if (pt.isInstanceOf[ProtoType] && !failure.isAmbiguous)
2394               // don't report the failure but return the tree unchanged. This
2395               // will cause a failure at the next level out, which usually gives
2396               // a better error message.
2397               tree
2398             else recover(failure.reason)
2399         }
2400       else recover(NoMatchingImplicits)
2401     }
2402 
2403     def adaptType(tp: Type): Tree = {
2404       val tree1 =
2405         if ((pt eq AnyTypeConstructorProto) || tp.typeParamSymbols.isEmpty) tree
2406         else {
2407           val tp1 =
2408             if (ctx.compilationUnit.isJava)
2409               // Cook raw type
2410               AppliedType(tree.tpe, tp.typeParams.map(Function.const(TypeBounds.empty)))
2411             else
2412               // Eta-expand higher-kinded type
2413               tree.tpe.EtaExpand(tp.typeParamSymbols)
2414           tree.withType(tp1)
2415         }
2416       if ((ctx.mode is Mode.Pattern) || tree1.tpe <:< pt) tree1
2417       else err.typeMismatch(tree1, pt)
2418     }
2419 
2420     /** If tree has an error type but no errors are reported yet, issue
2421      *  the error message stored in the type.
2422      *  One way this can happen is if implicit search causes symbols and types
2423      *  to be completed. The types are stored by `typedAhead` so that they can be
2424      *  retrieved later and thus avoid duplication of typechecking work.
2425      *  But if the implicit search causing the `typedAhead` fails locally but
2426      *  another alternative succeeds we can be left with an ErrorType in the
2427      *  tree that went unreported. A scenario where this happens is i1802.scala.
2428      */
2429     def ensureReported(tp: Type) = tp match {
2430       case err: ErrorType if !ctx.reporter.errorsReported => ctx.error(err.msg, tree.pos)
2431       case _ =>
2432     }
2433 
2434     tree match {
2435       case _: MemberDef | _: PackageDef | _: Import | _: WithoutTypeOrPos[_] => tree
2436       case _ => tree.tpe.widen match {
2437         case tp: FlexType =>
2438           ensureReported(tp)
2439           tree
2440         case ref: TermRef =>
2441           pt match {
2442             case pt: FunProto
2443             if pt.args.lengthCompare(1) > 0 && isUnary(ref) && ctx.canAutoTuple =>
2444               adaptInterpolated(tree, pt.tupled)
2445             case _ =>
2446               adaptOverloaded(ref)
2447           }
2448         case poly: PolyType if !(ctx.mode is Mode.Type) =>
2449           if (pt.isInstanceOf[PolyProto]) tree
2450           else {
2451             var typeArgs = tree match {
2452               case Select(qual, nme.CONSTRUCTOR) => qual.tpe.widenDealias.argTypesLo.map(TypeTree)
2453               case _ => Nil
2454             }
2455             if (typeArgs.isEmpty) typeArgs = constrained(poly, tree)._2
2456             convertNewGenericArray(
2457               adaptInterpolated(tree.appliedToTypeTrees(typeArgs), pt))
2458           }
2459         case wtp =>
2460           if (isStructuralTermSelect(tree)) adapt(handleStructural(tree), pt)
2461           else pt match {
2462             case pt: FunProto =>
2463               adaptToArgs(wtp, pt)
2464             case pt: PolyProto =>
2465               tryInsertApplyOrImplicit(tree, pt)(tree) // error will be reported in typedTypeApply
2466             case _ =>
2467               if (ctx.mode is Mode.Type) adaptType(tree.tpe)
2468               else adaptNoArgs(wtp)
2469           }
2470       }
2471     }
2472   }

2474   /** Check that `tree == x: pt` is typeable. Used when checking a pattern
2475     * against a selector of type `pt`. This implementation accounts for
2476     * user-defined definitions of `==`.
2477     *
2478     * Overwritten to no-op in ReTyper.
2479     */
2480   protected def checkEqualityEvidence(tree: tpd.Tree, pt: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) : Unit = {
2481     tree match {
2482       case _: RefTree | _: Literal
2483         if !isVarPattern(tree) &&
2484           !(tree.tpe <:< pt) (ctx.addMode(Mode.GADTflexible)) =>
2485         val cmp =
2486           untpd.Apply(
2487             untpd.Select(untpd.TypedSplice(tree), nme.EQ),
2488             untpd.TypedSplice(dummyTreeOfType(pt)))
2489         typedExpr(cmp, defn.BooleanType)
2490       case _ =>
2491     }
2492   }
